1
00:01:36,438 --> 00:01:37,480
Anjali!

2
00:01:37,563 --> 00:01:40,230
Your father will be here soon.
Come inside.

3
00:02:17,521 --> 00:02:19,563
Aunt and Anjali have been
worried about you at home.

4
00:02:20,188 --> 00:02:21,313
Why is your phone switched off?

5
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:23,605
Why do you look so tense?

6
00:02:25,021 --> 00:02:25,938
Pal…

7
00:02:26,021 --> 00:02:28,396
someone is following me.

8
00:02:28,521 --> 00:02:29,438
Following you?

9
00:02:29,521 --> 00:02:31,730
I didn't notice anyone.
There is no one here.

10
00:02:32,605 --> 00:02:34,230
Come, don't be suspicious.

11
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:36,021
Who would follow us anyway?

12
00:02:39,021 --> 00:02:39,896
- Pal…
- Yeah?

13
00:02:40,355 --> 00:02:41,396
We reached your house, you go home.

14
00:02:41,646 --> 00:02:43,438
That's OK, dude.
I'll accompany you till there.

15
00:02:43,730 --> 00:02:45,271
That's OK. You go home.

16
00:02:45,688 --> 00:02:46,938
Take the umbrella at least.

17
00:03:04,938 --> 00:03:07,230
Dad, I missed you, Dad!

18
00:03:10,855 --> 00:03:12,313
I miss you too, my dear!

19
00:03:13,813 --> 00:03:15,021
{\an8}So what happened at your school today?

20
00:03:15,105 --> 00:03:20,105
{\an8}Today, my teacher asked me
who our favorite hero is.

21
00:03:21,063 --> 00:03:26,938
{\an8}All my friends got it wrong,
naming people like Superman and Batman.

22
00:03:27,021 --> 00:03:29,396
{\an8}Oh! What was the right answer you gave?

23
00:03:29,521 --> 00:03:32,438
{\an8}I said my Father is my hero.

24
00:04:08,230 --> 00:04:10,521
<i>House number 34/18G, Borabanda.</i>

25
00:04:10,730 --> 00:04:13,063
<i>Opposite Bold and Beautiful beauty parlor.</i>

26
00:04:13,188 --> 00:04:15,521
- Name?
<i>- Aslam Ahmed… 62 years old.</i>

27
00:04:15,646 --> 00:04:16,563
Oh Allah!

28
00:04:37,521 --> 00:04:38,688
Look what has happened!

29
00:04:39,438 --> 00:04:41,396
He left us all.

30
00:04:50,855 --> 00:04:52,730
- Get some tea for everyone.
- OK.

31
00:04:52,813 --> 00:04:54,271
Why does the tent cost so much?

32
00:04:54,438 --> 00:04:55,896
You didn't give us enough chairs too!

33
00:04:55,980 --> 00:04:58,688
There isn't even a penny at home.
He passed away so suddenly!

34
00:04:58,938 --> 00:05:01,771
Aslam was very sharp in his childhood.

35
00:05:03,063 --> 00:05:06,563
He used to bunk the school prayer
and paint on the school walls.

36
00:05:06,646 --> 00:05:08,605
His paintings were awesome.

37
00:05:18,938 --> 00:05:20,021
There isn't even a penny at home.

38
00:05:20,105 --> 00:05:21,396
He left us all.

39
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:24,438
It was our Aslam who opened a
mechanic shop in Borabanda area.

40
00:05:24,521 --> 00:05:26,980
For miles around, his shop was
the only hope for a flat tire!

41
00:05:27,188 --> 00:05:28,396
He was in full demand!

42
00:05:28,855 --> 00:05:30,980
Only after he opened the mechanic shed…

43
00:05:31,230 --> 00:05:32,646
Aslam was a great man.

44
00:05:34,646 --> 00:05:39,730
Aslam's paintings were so beautiful.

45
00:05:39,938 --> 00:05:43,063
Shall I say something he
told me about you, Aunt?

46
00:05:44,063 --> 00:05:49,146
He said he couldn't sleep peacefully
without seeing your face before he slept.

47
00:05:53,021 --> 00:05:55,855
I still remember what he said
while showing me his wallet.

48
00:05:58,313 --> 00:05:59,896
Even if I don't have
money in my wallet,

49
00:06:01,230 --> 00:06:03,646
I'm a king as long as I
have my son's photo in it.

50
00:06:04,938 --> 00:06:08,980
I got the news that he passed
away from a stranger.

51
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:11,730
There are many people like me.

52
00:06:13,230 --> 00:06:15,521
All of them should know
about brother Aslam's demise.

53
00:06:15,813 --> 00:06:17,938
But we don't have any of their numbers.

54
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,813
You please do something.

55
00:06:20,355 --> 00:06:22,480
- Even I don't know their numbers.
- What do we do now?

56
00:06:24,855 --> 00:06:25,771
There is something we could do.

57
00:06:26,271 --> 00:06:27,688
We can publish an obituary
ad in the newspaper.

58
00:06:28,063 --> 00:06:29,105
Everyone will see it and come.

59
00:06:29,188 --> 00:06:31,563
How much will it cost to
publish an ad in the newspaper?

60
00:06:31,646 --> 00:06:35,021
{\an8}Rs.18,565 including GST with
20% discount. That's all!

61
00:06:35,105 --> 00:06:36,271
{\an8}- Oh!
- How do you know about it?

62
00:06:39,605 --> 00:06:44,021
We gave a similar ad when my
grandma passed away a week ago.

63
00:06:44,230 --> 00:06:46,521
Unfortunately, the same
thing happened to brother Aslam.

64
00:06:46,605 --> 00:06:48,271
That's why…

65
00:06:49,730 --> 00:06:51,021
Here's my donation of Rs. 500.

66
00:06:54,063 --> 00:06:55,980
- Everyone, please donate.
<i>- My plan has worked out.</i>

67
00:06:57,646 --> 00:07:00,355
{\an8}LATE. ASLAM BEG

68
00:07:21,313 --> 00:07:22,521
{\an8}FREEDOM

69
00:07:25,063 --> 00:07:26,021
Sir, please.

70
00:07:28,313 --> 00:07:29,188
Good morning, sir.

71
00:07:29,563 --> 00:07:30,688
Good morning, champ.

72
00:07:31,355 --> 00:07:32,355
Good morning, Mr. Sravan.

73
00:07:34,396 --> 00:07:35,771
Sir, the information is legit.

74
00:07:36,146 --> 00:07:37,813
But your source is not legit.

75
00:07:38,063 --> 00:07:40,230
So, I won't allow it.

76
00:07:40,313 --> 00:07:41,730
BANK SCAM

77
00:07:42,271 --> 00:07:43,521
Is it about the BBA bank scam, sir?

78
00:07:44,313 --> 00:07:47,188
Actually, the ones running BBA bank
have taken a loan of Rs. 3000 crores

79
00:07:47,271 --> 00:07:50,355
dividing it into 6 branches
and transferring funds from them.

80
00:07:50,438 --> 00:07:53,980
If we investigate from that angle,
I'm sure we'll find a solution.

81
00:07:54,355 --> 00:07:55,771
Oh, so now you're telling me what to do?

82
00:07:58,230 --> 00:07:59,355
I was just trying to help you.

83
00:07:59,438 --> 00:08:02,021
Did I ever help you in
making money off deaths?

84
00:08:02,688 --> 00:08:03,730
So, you don't do it either.

85
00:08:04,980 --> 00:08:07,021
Sir, we have to consider this.

86
00:08:10,438 --> 00:08:11,563
I think we are done.

87
00:08:14,688 --> 00:08:15,605
So, Jay.

88
00:08:16,021 --> 00:08:17,771
1000 ads in 6 months.

89
00:08:17,980 --> 00:08:20,146
Now, this is something
you should feel proud of.

90
00:08:20,605 --> 00:08:21,480
Do you know something?

91
00:08:21,563 --> 00:08:22,521
For the past twenty years…

92
00:08:22,855 --> 00:08:27,105
No print media house has a man like you
who can bring in so many obituary ads.

93
00:08:27,771 --> 00:08:29,605
- And there shouldn't be, sir.
- Why?

94
00:08:29,855 --> 00:08:32,146
Don't you know how much revenue
you have generated for the company?

95
00:08:32,355 --> 00:08:34,021
Man, this is commendable!

96
00:08:34,271 --> 00:08:36,063
It's not commendable, sir. It's terrible.

97
00:08:37,771 --> 00:08:39,021
All that aside, sir…

98
00:08:39,646 --> 00:08:41,688
Kindly promote me to the crime bureau.

99
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:44,438
- Please, sir.
- Ah! Sorry, Jay.

100
00:08:44,896 --> 00:08:47,563
Neither are you experienced
nor qualified for that.

101
00:08:47,646 --> 00:08:49,355
If you'd like, I can increase your pay.

102
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:51,355
Sir, please, sir.
Give me just one chance.

103
00:08:51,438 --> 00:08:52,313
Please, sir.

104
00:08:52,688 --> 00:08:54,188
I think we are done, Jay.

105
00:08:54,730 --> 00:08:55,688
Anything else?

106
00:09:02,313 --> 00:09:03,396
What? It didn't work?

107
00:09:04,938 --> 00:09:05,896
So, back to the same work?

108
00:09:07,771 --> 00:09:09,521
Hmm… I think you're done here.

109
00:09:10,313 --> 00:09:11,188
How is it possible?

110
00:09:13,855 --> 00:09:14,896
A new customer.

111
00:09:14,980 --> 00:09:16,563
It's been 15 minutes. Shall we start?

112
00:09:18,396 --> 00:09:20,313
{\an8}<i>One who is born must die.</i>

113
00:09:20,855 --> 00:09:23,146
{\an8}<i>And a dead one must be born again.</i>

114
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:28,438
<i>One must not grieve over</i>
<i>this inevitable cycle of life.</i>

115
00:09:52,771 --> 00:09:56,563
"Life is very short, forget yesterday!"

116
00:09:56,646 --> 00:09:59,563
"Realize the eighth wonder in you…
Purpose!"

117
00:09:59,688 --> 00:10:02,730
"Shove your worry up the dustbin."

118
00:10:02,813 --> 00:10:05,396
"Remember, you have only one life."

119
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:07,730
"Don't break your head,
life isn't a joke."

120
00:10:07,813 --> 00:10:10,313
{\an8}"You live till death but
don't live a dead life."

121
00:10:10,396 --> 00:10:12,688
"Don't be a fool."

122
00:10:12,771 --> 00:10:14,313
- Is that Satthi?
- Where are you?

123
00:10:14,396 --> 00:10:16,521
- We are having breakfast.
- I'm hungry too.

124
00:10:26,313 --> 00:10:27,396
Drink it, and you're gone.

125
00:10:27,646 --> 00:10:29,188
- Why? Isn't this water?
- No.

126
00:10:29,313 --> 00:10:31,605
The body stops working
after 15 seconds of drinking.

127
00:10:31,688 --> 00:10:33,646
- Oh no!
- And then the brain stops working.

128
00:10:33,730 --> 00:10:34,646
And then?

129
00:10:34,730 --> 00:10:36,688
You will lie here.
I'll have to cut you open.

130
00:10:36,771 --> 00:10:38,438
You must have told that a bit earlier.

131
00:10:40,396 --> 00:10:45,563
"Someday you would pass away,
you can't stop it with tears!"

132
00:10:45,646 --> 00:10:50,688
"Someday you'd be arriving again,
so pass away smiling!"

133
00:10:50,771 --> 00:10:55,980
{\an8}"Someday you would pass away,
you can't stop it with tears!"

134
00:10:56,063 --> 00:11:01,271
"Someday you'd be arriving again,
so pass away smiling!"

135
00:11:06,855 --> 00:11:07,813
But the stock just--

136
00:11:07,896 --> 00:11:09,980
They aren't chilled, don't you get it?

137
00:11:10,063 --> 00:11:11,230
- Stop it.
- What the hell is this?

138
00:11:12,605 --> 00:11:13,563
Are you Tony?

139
00:11:13,980 --> 00:11:15,605
- Son of Moroni?
- Yeah.

140
00:11:15,688 --> 00:11:18,896
Don't worry, boys.
He will sure end up at our place.

141
00:11:19,230 --> 00:11:21,771
- Why would I come?
- Everyone must come here one day.

142
00:11:22,021 --> 00:11:24,563
"Death wouldn't stop if you do!"

143
00:11:24,646 --> 00:11:25,521
"Yeah! Yeah!"

144
00:11:25,730 --> 00:11:27,855
{\an8}"Being anxious thinking about…"

145
00:11:27,938 --> 00:11:29,730
- Get in, sir.
- "it is wasting your life."

146
00:11:29,813 --> 00:11:30,730
"Move on!"

147
00:11:30,980 --> 00:11:32,438
"Listen, life is a delicacy!"

148
00:11:32,563 --> 00:11:35,605
"Don't search for your own death!"

149
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:38,271
"In your confusion and inebriation!"

150
00:11:38,355 --> 00:11:40,813
"Embrace yourself!
Life shouldn't be a sorry tale!"

151
00:11:40,896 --> 00:11:44,021
"It's a never-ending, gushing river!"

152
00:11:44,105 --> 00:11:46,271
- One masala dosa please.
- Okay, brother.

153
00:11:46,855 --> 00:11:48,021
Why the long face, dude?

154
00:11:48,105 --> 00:11:50,521
Is it about the crime reporter job?
He will give you.

155
00:12:02,355 --> 00:12:07,563
{\an8}"Someday you would pass away,
you can't stop it with tears!"

156
00:12:07,646 --> 00:12:12,730
"Someday you'd be arriving again,
so pass away smiling!"

157
00:12:12,813 --> 00:12:17,980
"Someday you would pass away,
you can't stop it with tears!"

158
00:12:18,063 --> 00:12:23,313
"Someday you'd be arriving again,
so pass away smiling!"

159
00:12:34,730 --> 00:12:35,813
Cheers!

160
00:12:36,771 --> 00:12:37,730
David bro…

161
00:12:38,021 --> 00:12:42,271
Why do you need the lighting, sprinklers,
and all this setup among these graves?

162
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:45,646
This is not just a graveyard,
this is their last resting place.

163
00:12:45,771 --> 00:12:48,271
People who come here cry only when
they come here for the first time.

164
00:12:48,355 --> 00:12:51,980
Later, they come to meet their loved ones.

165
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:56,271
They come to share their victory,
defeat, pain, and happiness.

166
00:12:56,938 --> 00:13:00,271
How peaceful should such a place be?

167
00:13:00,771 --> 00:13:02,605
Which is why I decorated this place.

168
00:13:02,896 --> 00:13:04,230
- Aunt is calling.
- Don't pick it up! Don't!

169
00:13:04,313 --> 00:13:05,646
I already did! Here, talk to her.

170
00:13:06,063 --> 00:13:08,521
Where are you, donkey!
With those three friends of yours?

171
00:13:09,438 --> 00:13:10,396
Yes, Aunt.

172
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:14,021
You're a working donkey, and
those three are jobless donkeys!

173
00:13:14,146 --> 00:13:16,396
<i>Make friends with people who</i>
<i>do something in their lives!</i>

174
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:18,230
Enough of roaming
around with those morons.

175
00:13:18,313 --> 00:13:19,188
Go home!

176
00:13:22,438 --> 00:13:24,271
- Is Mexican cheese dosa available?
- Available.

177
00:13:24,646 --> 00:13:26,021
- Give me one.
- Alright.

178
00:13:28,396 --> 00:13:30,813
<i>- Hey, what are you doing?</i>
- I am eating, why?

179
00:13:31,438 --> 00:13:33,230
<i>OK, a new customer has come up.</i>
<i>Want to pay a visit?</i>

180
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:34,355
His name?

181
00:13:34,438 --> 00:13:36,813
<i>His name is Achyuth Sharma. 38 years old.</i>

182
00:13:37,063 --> 00:13:37,938
Okay.

183
00:13:39,355 --> 00:13:41,188
Achyuth Sharma…

184
00:13:57,688 --> 00:14:01,688
You left us so young, my boy!

185
00:14:01,896 --> 00:14:06,188
Why did that wretched wire take you,
my son!

186
00:14:06,730 --> 00:14:09,105
Oh, son!

187
00:14:09,188 --> 00:14:10,563
I'm unable to believe it even now.

188
00:14:10,688 --> 00:14:12,230
This is a regrettable occurrence.

189
00:14:12,563 --> 00:14:14,355
I used to visit the temple just for him.

190
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:16,230
Mr. Achyuth had a magical voice.

191
00:14:16,313 --> 00:14:19,313
Our spiritual gathering is full
from 6 pm to 7 pm every day.

192
00:14:19,438 --> 00:14:22,105
Now that he's left us,
it's painful to even visit the temple.

193
00:14:22,230 --> 00:14:23,355
- Give it to me, I will serve.
- God always…

194
00:14:23,438 --> 00:14:24,813
…takes good people away too soon.

195
00:14:31,563 --> 00:14:34,521
I've told him so many times to buy a car.

196
00:14:34,605 --> 00:14:36,021
He brushed it off,
saying he could always take the Metro.

197
00:15:41,438 --> 00:15:42,688
I wonder why the child is not crying!

198
00:15:45,521 --> 00:15:47,105
Her pain might become
unbearable if she doesn't let it out.

199
00:15:47,980 --> 00:15:49,396
So unbearable that she can't take it.

200
00:15:51,438 --> 00:15:53,563
She is too young to understand… maybe.

201
00:16:24,313 --> 00:16:25,855
I think I was just seven
years old back then.

202
00:16:26,105 --> 00:16:28,188
The neighbors woke me up that morning.

203
00:16:28,521 --> 00:16:32,063
<i>I walked out and saw my</i>
<i>parents lying on the hall floor.</i>

204
00:16:32,230 --> 00:16:34,480
<i>I didn't understand why they</i>
<i>were lying there like that.</i>

205
00:16:34,605 --> 00:16:37,605
I wanted to wake them up,
but I wasn't allowed.

206
00:16:39,438 --> 00:16:42,438
Uncle, why did this happen to my parents?

207
00:16:43,396 --> 00:16:45,563
<i>But no one answered me.</i>

208
00:16:45,730 --> 00:16:49,605
<i>I know what death means,</i>
<i>but I have never experienced it.</i>

209
00:16:51,938 --> 00:16:53,271
I was in a state of shock.

210
00:16:57,063 --> 00:16:58,355
<i>That's when my aunt arrived.</i>

211
00:17:00,896 --> 00:17:04,980
<i>She sat silently beside me,</i>
<i>not uttering a single word.</i>

212
00:17:05,980 --> 00:17:08,646
<i>From then on, my aunt</i>
<i>started behaving strange.</i>

213
00:17:11,063 --> 00:17:12,355
<i>I didn't understand anything.</i>

214
00:17:14,021 --> 00:17:15,771
Is that how you treat children, lady?

215
00:17:15,855 --> 00:17:18,271
We've been noticing that you've
always been scolding the poor child.

216
00:17:18,355 --> 00:17:22,563
<i>That's when my aunt began scolding me,</i>
<i>and she kept going afterward.</i>

217
00:17:28,230 --> 00:17:29,896
I shouted so hard that…

218
00:17:31,313 --> 00:17:36,063
I didn't even know when that
shout transformed into sobbing.

219
00:17:38,188 --> 00:17:39,646
That's when my aunt cried.

220
00:17:40,271 --> 00:17:43,563
<i>It was then that I understood</i>
<i>why my aunt scolded me.</i>

221
00:18:05,063 --> 00:18:08,396
If the people who are close to us die,
we must vent it out.

222
00:18:14,230 --> 00:18:17,021
Otherwise, the pain inside
would become unbearable.

223
00:18:19,230 --> 00:18:20,646
So unbearable that we can't take it.

224
00:18:20,855 --> 00:18:27,271
"The sadness inside is
searching for the reason."

225
00:18:27,605 --> 00:18:31,271
"But tears don't roll down."

226
00:18:34,188 --> 00:18:38,146
"Where did the sorrow disappear?"

227
00:18:38,230 --> 00:18:40,146
It's been two years
since her mother died.

228
00:18:40,563 --> 00:18:42,896
Since then,
her father has been her whole world.

229
00:18:43,146 --> 00:18:45,896
Unfortunately, he too passed
away, leaving the child alone.

230
00:18:47,021 --> 00:18:52,855
"The tender heart is
carrying a heavy burden,"

231
00:18:53,605 --> 00:18:59,396
"how can one unburden it?"

232
00:19:00,230 --> 00:19:06,271
"What God writes,"

233
00:19:06,980 --> 00:19:12,855
"can that fate be changed?"

234
00:19:18,396 --> 00:19:21,313
"I'll be your friend."

235
00:19:21,771 --> 00:19:25,021
"I'll become your strength."

236
00:19:25,105 --> 00:19:27,980
{\an8}"I'll become the answer
you are looking for."

237
00:19:28,396 --> 00:19:31,646
"I'll be the peace you're longing for."

238
00:19:31,730 --> 00:19:34,563
"Though steps falter…"

239
00:19:34,896 --> 00:19:38,313
"I'll always support you."

240
00:19:38,396 --> 00:19:40,230
- "Even if you get scared in your sleep,"
- Don't worry, Anjali.

241
00:19:40,438 --> 00:19:41,646
I'm your father's friend.

242
00:19:41,730 --> 00:19:46,021
"I'm always there for you."

243
00:19:46,105 --> 00:19:48,771
Your father and I used
to meet in the temple.

244
00:19:51,313 --> 00:19:53,105
Your father used to sing very well.

245
00:19:55,188 --> 00:19:57,396
Your father used to talk
about you all the time.

246
00:19:58,980 --> 00:20:00,396
He was always proud of you.

247
00:20:09,313 --> 00:20:10,313
Sorry, Anjali.

248
00:20:10,980 --> 00:20:12,605
Your father never spoke to me.

249
00:20:14,230 --> 00:20:15,563
I don't even know him.

250
00:20:17,230 --> 00:20:18,855
It has become a habit to lie.

251
00:20:20,896 --> 00:20:21,938
That's why I lied.

252
00:20:26,396 --> 00:20:28,396
I understand your pain, Anjali.

253
00:20:30,896 --> 00:20:33,980
My aunt said that sharing your
pain helps ease the burden.

254
00:20:34,896 --> 00:20:37,855
That's why I tried to talk something.

255
00:20:39,605 --> 00:20:40,480
I'm sorry.

256
00:21:04,771 --> 00:21:08,271
Uncle, why did this happen to my father?

257
00:21:13,771 --> 00:21:16,896
'Uncle, why did this
happen to my parents?'

258
00:22:30,605 --> 00:22:32,105
The wires need to be checked as well.

259
00:22:32,188 --> 00:22:33,771
{\an8}But madam, this is just an accident!

260
00:22:39,730 --> 00:22:42,730
{\an8}- It's not an accident until we say it is.
- Okay, madam.

261
00:22:42,813 --> 00:22:43,938
{\an8}- Get it?
- Sure, madam.

262
00:22:53,521 --> 00:22:54,563
Please have tea.

263
00:22:55,396 --> 00:22:57,605
- Thank you.
- He used to play for an hour every day.

264
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:00,730
Everyone watched only
Vikranth for that one hour.

265
00:23:01,271 --> 00:23:02,563
What a player he was!

266
00:23:07,146 --> 00:23:09,146
Vikranth and I used to
work in the same bank.

267
00:23:09,230 --> 00:23:12,980
After the Metro started, we became
close friends while traveling together.

268
00:23:17,063 --> 00:23:19,355
Sir, Vikranth was scheduled to
testify in court tomorrow at 11:00 a.m.

269
00:23:19,438 --> 00:23:21,021
against the BBA company scam.

270
00:23:21,146 --> 00:23:22,105
What is this sudden accident?

271
00:23:22,188 --> 00:23:24,605
Had Vikranth testified,
the BBA company would have collapsed.

272
00:23:24,688 --> 00:23:27,355
So, do you think it's the owners of the
bank who orchestrated Vikranth's murder?

273
00:23:27,438 --> 00:23:28,563
Guys, please.

274
00:23:28,855 --> 00:23:31,313
{\an8}This is a purely an accident.
Nothing more than that.

275
00:23:31,396 --> 00:23:33,063
Sir, were your cops with
Vikranth to protect him…

276
00:23:33,146 --> 00:23:34,855
or just to report what's happening?

277
00:23:35,146 --> 00:23:38,313
Hey, look.
My boys were with Vikranth 24x7.

278
00:23:38,521 --> 00:23:42,230
We can save him if someone attacks him
but what can we do about a lightning hit?

279
00:23:43,063 --> 00:23:45,521
Sir, looks like lightning
struck him right on the head.

280
00:23:45,605 --> 00:23:48,105
{\an8}I'll let ACP Seetha answer that.

281
00:23:48,438 --> 00:23:50,230
{\an8}Her team is handling this case.

282
00:23:50,438 --> 00:23:52,188
{\an8}She can confirm that this is an accident.

283
00:23:52,271 --> 00:23:54,188
{\an8}Madam, are you confirming
that this is an accident?

284
00:23:54,730 --> 00:23:56,396
Maybe it is. Maybe it's not.

285
00:23:56,730 --> 00:23:59,605
We can confirm anything
after a thorough investigation.

286
00:24:42,188 --> 00:24:43,063
<i>What, man?</i>

287
00:24:43,146 --> 00:24:46,313
Hey, Achyuth Sharma died
a few days ago, right?

288
00:24:46,605 --> 00:24:48,521
I'm talking about
that small girl's father.

289
00:24:48,605 --> 00:24:50,438
<i>- Yes.</i>
- How did he die?

290
00:24:50,521 --> 00:24:52,438
<i>While jogging in the morning,</i>
<i>he stopped by a temple on the way.</i>

291
00:24:52,521 --> 00:24:53,980
<i>He was accidentally</i>
<i>electrocuted there and died.</i>

292
00:24:55,646 --> 00:24:57,730
No. That's not an accident.

293
00:24:57,855 --> 00:24:59,438
<i>- Then?</i>
- It's a murder.

294
00:24:59,730 --> 00:25:01,646
{\an8}When we say it's an accident,
you ask us why not murder.

295
00:25:01,855 --> 00:25:03,771
{\an8}When we say it's an murder,
you ask us why not an accident.

296
00:25:03,855 --> 00:25:06,605
Let's not assume things.
Nothing is concrete yet.

297
00:25:14,896 --> 00:25:18,396
It's painful if our loved ones die.

298
00:25:20,105 --> 00:25:23,521
But it will be terrible if we
don't know how they died.

299
00:25:23,980 --> 00:25:26,771
Will you prove an accident to be murder
because that little girl asked you?

300
00:25:26,896 --> 00:25:28,063
Are you out of your mind?

301
00:25:28,188 --> 00:25:29,230
Not just him,

302
00:25:30,563 --> 00:25:35,188
even police officer Seetha
said that maybe it isn't an accident.

303
00:25:35,730 --> 00:25:36,605
Take a look.

304
00:25:38,146 --> 00:25:40,980
<i>But all I can say is that,</i>
<i>it's too much of a coincidence.</i>

305
00:25:41,146 --> 00:25:42,355
Exactly! Coincidence.

306
00:25:44,313 --> 00:25:45,188
What, man?

307
00:25:45,271 --> 00:25:47,105
If you speak in English
like that police woman,

308
00:25:47,271 --> 00:25:48,438
will an accident become a murder?

309
00:25:49,438 --> 00:25:51,980
Alright, let's consider it an accident.
But how many times can it happen?

310
00:25:52,646 --> 00:25:54,771
How is it possible that
both accidents are so similar?

311
00:25:54,855 --> 00:25:55,855
Deaths caused by falls from buildings,

312
00:25:55,938 --> 00:25:57,730
or being run over by
trucks tend to appear alike.

313
00:26:04,730 --> 00:26:05,813
Alright.

314
00:26:06,313 --> 00:26:09,396
But what if two people fall under the
same truck within a span of three days?

315
00:26:10,688 --> 00:26:14,271
That's the bad luck of the lorry driver.

316
00:26:14,605 --> 00:26:16,021
But what if it's not his bad luck?

317
00:26:20,438 --> 00:26:21,521
So is it the same killer?

318
00:26:23,271 --> 00:26:25,105
So, you are saying that both
cases have equal chances.

319
00:26:25,438 --> 00:26:30,396
If you add up Seetha madam's
50% and my 50%, it's 100%, right?

320
00:26:39,688 --> 00:26:41,313
See how many cops are around her!

321
00:26:41,396 --> 00:26:43,480
If I say I witnessed last night's murder,
they'll take me to her.

322
00:26:49,063 --> 00:26:51,438
Madam, he says he has seen something.

323
00:26:51,688 --> 00:26:53,021
{\an8}He's afraid to tell you.

324
00:26:53,938 --> 00:26:55,938
{\an8}OK, I'll talk to him. You go.

325
00:26:56,021 --> 00:26:56,938
OK, madam.

326
00:26:58,646 --> 00:26:59,563
{\an8}Your name?

327
00:26:59,730 --> 00:27:01,146
I'm Jay from Swechha newspaper, madam.

328
00:27:01,563 --> 00:27:03,646
{\an8}OK. What did you see? Tell me.

329
00:27:04,063 --> 00:27:04,938
I didn't see anything, madam.

330
00:27:06,105 --> 00:27:07,980
I came to talk to you
about something important.

331
00:27:08,396 --> 00:27:10,396
- What the hell?
- What you said was right.

332
00:27:10,563 --> 00:27:12,438
What happened to Vikranth is
definitely not an accident, madam.

333
00:27:13,605 --> 00:27:15,021
Madam, sign here.

334
00:27:17,271 --> 00:27:18,646
'Why is he here?'

335
00:27:21,396 --> 00:27:22,438
What are you doing here?

336
00:27:22,521 --> 00:27:23,813
Well just a…

337
00:27:25,813 --> 00:27:26,938
Do you know him?

338
00:27:27,063 --> 00:27:28,605
How can I not know him, madam?

339
00:27:28,813 --> 00:27:30,438
He always shows up
wherever there's a dead body.

340
00:27:31,188 --> 00:27:32,480
Madam, it's not like that.

341
00:27:32,646 --> 00:27:34,480
What you are suspecting is right.

342
00:27:34,563 --> 00:27:35,771
I too feel that it's a murder, madam.

343
00:27:36,771 --> 00:27:37,688
How do you know?

344
00:27:37,771 --> 00:27:42,813
Because, in a similar incident, a man
named Mr. Achyuth died in an accident

345
00:27:42,896 --> 00:27:44,563
about three to five kilometers
from here, Madam.

346
00:27:44,646 --> 00:27:46,105
Madam, the Commissioner is calling.

347
00:27:48,563 --> 00:27:49,480
{\an8}One minute.

348
00:27:51,646 --> 00:27:52,563
{\an8}<i>Jai Hind,</i> sir.

349
00:27:53,855 --> 00:27:54,730
Sure, sir.

350
00:27:55,355 --> 00:27:57,938
Sir, one week is far too little time.

351
00:27:58,938 --> 00:27:59,855
Okay, sir.

352
00:28:00,980 --> 00:28:02,605
I'll close the case in a week.

353
00:28:03,646 --> 00:28:04,646
{\an8}<i>Jai Hind.</i>

354
00:28:06,313 --> 00:28:07,855
- Madam, please listen to me--
- Madam!

355
00:28:08,605 --> 00:28:09,480
Madam…

356
00:28:09,646 --> 00:28:11,605
- Please try to understand, madam.
- Are you--

357
00:28:11,688 --> 00:28:14,105
- Actually, if we compare both the cases--
- Cut the crap!

358
00:28:14,605 --> 00:28:16,146
{\an8}Report it to the local police station.

359
00:28:16,230 --> 00:28:17,438
- Hey, move.
- Madam, police station?

360
00:28:17,521 --> 00:28:19,146
Who's going to listen to me
at the station?

361
00:28:19,230 --> 00:28:20,105
- Please, madam.
- Come.

362
00:28:20,188 --> 00:28:21,521
- I've found two or three clues.
- Get it done!

363
00:28:21,605 --> 00:28:23,188
Trust me, madam.
I just need two minutes of your time.

364
00:28:23,271 --> 00:28:24,938
Just give me two minutes. Please…

365
00:28:31,813 --> 00:28:32,980
Chotu, bring me a tea.

366
00:28:34,438 --> 00:28:36,813
{\an8}The investigation ended
before it even started.

367
00:28:39,063 --> 00:28:40,396
Who said it ended?

368
00:28:42,355 --> 00:28:43,813
{\an8}So, when will it be over, brother?

369
00:28:44,938 --> 00:28:47,563
It's over when I say it's over.

370
00:28:48,563 --> 00:28:49,438
So, what's next?

371
00:28:50,396 --> 00:28:51,980
Chotu, want to hear a story?

372
00:28:53,771 --> 00:28:57,271
In the 14th century, there was
a king named Anjaneya Varma.

373
00:28:57,730 --> 00:29:01,938
He used to sense problems early
and solve them for everyone.

374
00:29:02,188 --> 00:29:04,188
The people used to be very happy.

375
00:29:04,563 --> 00:29:08,021
But there was always a question about
how the king solved their problems.

376
00:29:08,688 --> 00:29:09,646
{\an8}How did he?

377
00:29:10,938 --> 00:29:12,188
{\an8}Someone used to inform him.

378
00:29:17,021 --> 00:29:19,980
He is the one who can help us now.

379
00:29:20,313 --> 00:29:21,188
Who is he?

380
00:29:21,730 --> 00:29:22,688
- Chotu.
- Bro?

381
00:29:22,771 --> 00:29:23,730
Bring the tea now.

382
00:29:35,396 --> 00:29:36,313
Thanks.

383
00:29:36,688 --> 00:29:39,730
Uncle, I need to talk to you.

384
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:41,855
Money first.

385
00:29:46,063 --> 00:29:47,021
No.

386
00:29:47,188 --> 00:29:48,771
- Only coins!
- Huh!

387
00:29:50,813 --> 00:29:51,855
- Have any?
- Here, give them to him.

388
00:29:51,938 --> 00:29:54,188
Notes tear. Coins don't!

389
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:55,980
- Oh.
- Oh…

390
00:29:58,688 --> 00:29:59,688
Yes.

391
00:30:00,021 --> 00:30:01,313
How can I help?

392
00:30:01,646 --> 00:30:04,021
Do you know that a
guy died here yesterday?

393
00:30:04,813 --> 00:30:07,896
Huh! Very nice man.

394
00:30:09,688 --> 00:30:12,771
Every morning, jogging, praying.

395
00:30:14,438 --> 00:30:17,188
Then he puts five rupees in my tumbler.

396
00:30:17,271 --> 00:30:23,438
Did you observe anything unusual or
suspicious at the time of his death?

397
00:30:32,480 --> 00:30:33,396
You see that?

398
00:30:35,355 --> 00:30:40,063
Every three days, a short guy…
Mehmood comes.

399
00:30:40,563 --> 00:30:42,146
- Repair.
- OK…

400
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:43,646
What is today's date?

401
00:30:44,438 --> 00:30:46,438
- 15th.
- Ah!

402
00:30:47,480 --> 00:30:48,480
Yes.

403
00:30:49,021 --> 00:30:52,605
Last 3 days… even yesterday…

404
00:30:53,355 --> 00:30:55,646
One tall man came…

405
00:30:55,730 --> 00:30:58,230
He checked but did not repair.

406
00:30:58,688 --> 00:31:00,105
He prayed.

407
00:31:00,813 --> 00:31:04,105
And go to the other side and observe.

408
00:31:05,188 --> 00:31:06,188
What did he observe?

409
00:31:06,605 --> 00:31:07,688
The temple.

410
00:31:08,355 --> 00:31:10,188
He observed for a long time.

411
00:31:12,271 --> 00:31:13,896
'He used to watch the temple?'

412
00:31:14,313 --> 00:31:17,313
So, was the electrician present
here even when Vikranth died?

413
00:31:17,730 --> 00:31:18,730
Yes!

414
00:31:21,105 --> 00:31:22,021
Yes…

415
00:31:23,980 --> 00:31:25,063
Yes…

416
00:31:27,230 --> 00:31:29,021
And I saw more.

417
00:31:30,771 --> 00:31:31,730
What did you see, uncle?

418
00:31:32,813 --> 00:31:34,938
When Vikranth died…

419
00:31:47,938 --> 00:31:49,188
He smiled!

420
00:31:58,563 --> 00:32:00,396
- Greetings, sir.
- Look, Basheer…

421
00:32:00,605 --> 00:32:02,646
Officer Seetha is investigating this case.

422
00:32:02,813 --> 00:32:05,480
- If we get caught…
- You wouldn't, sir.

423
00:32:05,563 --> 00:32:07,271
How can you be so sure?

424
00:32:08,021 --> 00:32:11,563
You gave the contract to an
extraordinary person, sir.

425
00:32:11,896 --> 00:32:13,105
You gave it to Saadhu.

426
00:32:21,438 --> 00:32:23,813
- Could you describe his appearance?
- Yes.

427
00:32:25,271 --> 00:32:26,480
He was wearing a khaki shirt,

428
00:32:30,771 --> 00:32:31,730
he was bald headed,

429
00:32:34,355 --> 00:32:35,646
and powered glasses…

430
00:32:37,688 --> 00:32:40,521
And his left leg had a problem
like it was affected by polio.

431
00:32:47,188 --> 00:32:50,438
There is perfection in Saadhu's work.

432
00:32:51,188 --> 00:32:53,313
<i>Absolute perfection.</i>

433
00:33:05,021 --> 00:33:06,688
He is like a shadow.

434
00:33:06,813 --> 00:33:09,480
No one can catch him or escape from him.

435
00:33:20,355 --> 00:33:22,605
Death doesn't have a form, sir.

436
00:33:23,021 --> 00:33:28,188
Once Sadhu sets his eyes on someone,
not even the Almighty can save him.

437
00:34:02,980 --> 00:34:07,313
To tell you in simple words,
no one knows that he even exists.

438
00:34:07,646 --> 00:34:11,063
{\an8}THE FINAL JOURNEY

439
00:34:19,563 --> 00:34:20,521
Anji…

440
00:34:20,730 --> 00:34:22,313
We have something the police don't.

441
00:34:22,396 --> 00:34:23,271
What is that?

442
00:34:24,605 --> 00:34:25,605
Second crime scene.

443
00:34:26,396 --> 00:34:27,396
Sorry you are wrong.

444
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:29,605
This is first crime scene.
You forgot.

445
00:34:54,313 --> 00:34:55,938
What are you thinking?

446
00:34:56,730 --> 00:34:57,688
Let's search.

447
00:34:58,063 --> 00:34:59,146
What do we search for?

448
00:34:59,605 --> 00:35:00,896
For a beggar.

449
00:35:00,980 --> 00:35:02,521
You don't need a beggar every time.

450
00:35:02,646 --> 00:35:03,688
We just need a giver.

451
00:35:04,938 --> 00:35:07,146
Why would they give us the CCTV footage?

452
00:35:08,271 --> 00:35:09,605
We don't need it even if they do.

453
00:35:09,855 --> 00:35:11,188
Huh? Why so?

454
00:35:12,063 --> 00:35:13,521
You can't see the temple in that camera.

455
00:35:14,271 --> 00:35:17,396
But the security guard who
sits there can see it clearly.

456
00:35:17,521 --> 00:35:18,438
Wow.

457
00:35:18,563 --> 00:35:20,438
- Well done, Tintin.
- Thanks.

458
00:35:21,146 --> 00:35:22,688
- Let's inquire.
- Huh?

459
00:35:22,771 --> 00:35:23,688
Wait.

460
00:35:23,771 --> 00:35:24,938
This is his morning shift.

461
00:35:25,313 --> 00:35:26,896
Mr. Achyuth passed away
in the early hours.

462
00:35:27,105 --> 00:35:29,521
So we have to meet the
security guard in the night shift.

463
00:35:29,605 --> 00:35:32,146
- Got it?
- Wow! Awesome!

464
00:35:32,313 --> 00:35:35,480
Are you so smart since childhood or have
you developed because of the freebies?

465
00:35:35,646 --> 00:35:37,896
Necessity is the mother
of all the inventions.

466
00:35:38,063 --> 00:35:39,605
OK. Who is he?

467
00:35:39,688 --> 00:35:41,355
Come, I'll tell you a story.

468
00:35:47,396 --> 00:35:48,521
Hey! The security guard!

469
00:35:49,480 --> 00:35:50,938
Uncle! One minute!

470
00:35:51,396 --> 00:35:52,271
Greetings uncle.

471
00:35:52,355 --> 00:35:55,938
We came to talk about Mr. Achyuth,
who died near the temple.

472
00:35:56,355 --> 00:35:58,563
- Who are you?
- Insurance company.

473
00:35:59,396 --> 00:36:02,855
The cops suspect that his death
wasn't an accident, but a murder.

474
00:36:03,105 --> 00:36:04,605
We wanted to know if
you noticed something.

475
00:36:05,438 --> 00:36:06,521
Before this job…

476
00:36:06,605 --> 00:36:09,021
I used to work as a security guard
in the bank where he used to work.

477
00:36:09,105 --> 00:36:10,313
He was a very good man.

478
00:36:11,521 --> 00:36:14,021
I don't think anyone hated
him enough to kill him.

479
00:36:14,188 --> 00:36:16,855
Did you see anything
around this place that day?

480
00:36:17,605 --> 00:36:20,313
A bald man… wearing
high-powered glasses…

481
00:36:20,396 --> 00:36:22,188
Yes! Polio in the left leg.

482
00:36:22,355 --> 00:36:25,563
- Yes, that's right. Polio in the left leg.
- He used to stand there.

483
00:36:26,688 --> 00:36:27,813
He used to look there.

484
00:36:28,271 --> 00:36:29,938
How long has he been there?

485
00:36:30,563 --> 00:36:32,021
About a month.

486
00:36:32,313 --> 00:36:33,646
- 30 days?
- Yes.

487
00:36:37,938 --> 00:36:39,021
He used to come from there.

488
00:36:39,271 --> 00:36:40,646
He always took the same route back.

489
00:36:44,063 --> 00:36:45,896
- Here…
- Too many roads this side!

490
00:36:46,396 --> 00:36:47,896
There are no CCTV cameras here either.

491
00:36:48,813 --> 00:36:50,563
He could vanish from
here without a trace.

492
00:36:50,980 --> 00:36:51,896
What do we do now?

493
00:36:53,896 --> 00:36:59,313
If the security guard saw him,
maybe someone else did too.

494
00:36:59,688 --> 00:37:01,730
That's right. How do we catch him now?

495
00:37:02,605 --> 00:37:04,438
Come to Mr. Achyuth's house
at 10:00 a.m. tomorrow.

496
00:37:04,730 --> 00:37:05,730
I will also come there.

497
00:37:07,688 --> 00:37:09,938
Not possible, man.
Madam won't meet anyone at home.

498
00:37:10,021 --> 00:37:11,438
- Don't you understand?
- Just two minutes!

499
00:37:11,521 --> 00:37:13,188
- I'll go inside and talk to her.
- Not here, come to the office.

500
00:37:13,271 --> 00:37:15,105
Sunil! What's happening?

501
00:37:15,188 --> 00:37:17,438
See ma'am,
he wants to meet you right here.

502
00:37:21,563 --> 00:37:23,271
- Good morning, ma'am.
- Good morning.

503
00:37:23,605 --> 00:37:24,813
- Jay, right?
- Yes, ma'am.

504
00:37:25,396 --> 00:37:28,146
{\an8}If you want to talk
about an unrelated case,

505
00:37:28,438 --> 00:37:31,313
{\an8}you shouldn't be talking to me,
but at the local police station.

506
00:37:32,230 --> 00:37:33,396
Not about that, ma'am.

507
00:37:33,771 --> 00:37:34,646
{\an8}Then?

508
00:37:35,230 --> 00:37:37,605
{\an8}Let's talk on the way, ma'am. It would
be good if we talk sitting somewhere.

509
00:37:38,021 --> 00:37:39,271
{\an8}Please sit in, madam.

510
00:37:41,605 --> 00:37:43,813
Jay, I am so sorry about yesterday.

511
00:37:45,063 --> 00:37:47,146
Mr. Murthy shouldn't
have pushed you like that.

512
00:37:47,438 --> 00:37:48,355
Sorry.

513
00:37:48,438 --> 00:37:49,396
It's OK, ma'am.

514
00:37:49,980 --> 00:37:51,063
Your doubt is correct, ma'am.

515
00:37:51,438 --> 00:37:53,188
Mr. Vikranth was definitely murdered.

516
00:37:53,855 --> 00:37:54,938
How do you know?

517
00:37:55,188 --> 00:37:56,480
Madam had a doubt, right?

518
00:37:56,730 --> 00:38:01,396
Ma'am, if we look into the details
of the BBA bank and their call list…

519
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:04,188
Maybe we might get some case details…

520
00:38:04,313 --> 00:38:06,563
Oh, you are already looking into it!

521
00:38:06,980 --> 00:38:07,855
Super, super.

522
00:38:07,938 --> 00:38:10,271
Sunil bro, there is a road block here.

523
00:38:10,355 --> 00:38:11,355
Take a right.

524
00:38:12,521 --> 00:38:13,688
What do you want, Jay?

525
00:38:14,188 --> 00:38:15,146
Not just me, ma'am…

526
00:38:16,188 --> 00:38:17,813
Everyone wants something, ma'am.

527
00:38:18,605 --> 00:38:20,355
There… look at her.

528
00:38:20,688 --> 00:38:21,813
She wants money.

529
00:38:21,980 --> 00:38:24,230
Look at that person…
perhaps newly married.

530
00:38:24,313 --> 00:38:25,563
He wants peace of mind.

531
00:38:26,021 --> 00:38:26,938
Take a left, bro.

532
00:38:29,188 --> 00:38:30,896
And you want to be a dancer.

533
00:38:30,980 --> 00:38:32,521
Similarly, I want to
become a crime reporter.

534
00:38:32,688 --> 00:38:34,313
It's not a wish that was born recently.

535
00:38:34,563 --> 00:38:36,438
It's a wish that was born
when I was a kid.

536
00:38:38,396 --> 00:38:40,646
Stop to the left, brother.
It's a little shade there.

537
00:38:40,980 --> 00:38:42,188
Where are we, Sunil?

538
00:38:42,271 --> 00:38:45,688
I don't know madam. He guided me here.

539
00:38:45,855 --> 00:38:47,063
What non-sense?

540
00:38:47,188 --> 00:38:48,480
Park the car under the tree.

541
00:38:48,938 --> 00:38:49,980
Go away! Go away!

542
00:38:50,063 --> 00:38:52,355
Buddy, how come you got
down from a police car?

543
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:55,605
Would you expect a cop to step out of a
funeral van instead of a police vehicle?

544
00:38:56,980 --> 00:38:58,813
Some policemen are here.
I'll call you back.

545
00:39:00,980 --> 00:39:02,646
Sit down. I'll call my brother-in-law.

546
00:39:08,938 --> 00:39:10,896
- Hello, sir. My name is Ramu.
- Hi.

547
00:39:10,980 --> 00:39:11,896
- Hi.
- Hi.

548
00:39:12,105 --> 00:39:12,980
Sit down.

549
00:39:14,313 --> 00:39:16,063
- We belong to the same village.
- OK.

550
00:39:16,396 --> 00:39:17,271
Tell me.

551
00:39:17,438 --> 00:39:19,688
Did you notice any difference
in Mr. Achyuth's behavior?

552
00:39:19,771 --> 00:39:20,855
Since last 30 days?

553
00:39:21,313 --> 00:39:22,521
Nothing like that, sir.

554
00:39:22,646 --> 00:39:25,271
Brother's death was only by accident.
There's no other angle to it.

555
00:39:25,688 --> 00:39:27,521
Even a small detail might be of help.

556
00:39:28,396 --> 00:39:29,521
Think about it once.

557
00:39:33,438 --> 00:39:35,730
Sir, in the last two weeks,

558
00:39:36,188 --> 00:39:37,896
Achyuth missed two accidents.

559
00:39:39,605 --> 00:39:41,063
- What happened?
- One day…

560
00:39:41,438 --> 00:39:42,563
On his way home,

561
00:39:42,855 --> 00:39:45,438
he couldn't see the manhole
opened because of the rain.

562
00:39:46,021 --> 00:39:48,313
He was lucky that he
only put his leg in it.

563
00:39:48,730 --> 00:39:52,355
Another time, someone pushed him
from the stairs of the Metro station.

564
00:39:52,688 --> 00:39:54,480
Luckily, the person
next to him caught him.

565
00:39:54,813 --> 00:39:56,355
But brother was very scared.

566
00:39:56,813 --> 00:39:57,980
Didn't you have any doubt?

567
00:39:58,438 --> 00:39:59,938
What's there to doubt?

568
00:40:00,688 --> 00:40:03,188
It's just someone's negligence.
That's all.

569
00:40:07,605 --> 00:40:09,438
Okay. Anything else?

570
00:40:14,521 --> 00:40:16,021
Even if you don't think it's important,

571
00:40:16,105 --> 00:40:19,563
did you notice any change
in his routine life or behavior?

572
00:40:19,813 --> 00:40:22,230
Sir, I don't know if
it's important or not,

573
00:40:22,855 --> 00:40:23,938
but for the last 15 days,

574
00:40:24,563 --> 00:40:26,021
he said someone was following him.

575
00:40:26,105 --> 00:40:27,146
I also checked.

576
00:40:27,396 --> 00:40:28,396
But I didn't notice anything like that.

577
00:40:34,771 --> 00:40:35,688
Anything else?

578
00:40:36,271 --> 00:40:37,146
That's all.

579
00:40:37,980 --> 00:40:38,855
Nothing else.

580
00:40:39,771 --> 00:40:42,730
If you get any information, call
us immediately and let us know.

581
00:40:42,813 --> 00:40:43,813
Sure.

582
00:40:58,646 --> 00:40:59,563
I don't know, child.

583
00:41:01,021 --> 00:41:04,980
I don't know the answer to the
question you asked, but I'll find out.

584
00:41:06,855 --> 00:41:08,521
I'm facing a highly complex issue now.

585
00:41:09,396 --> 00:41:10,480
But I'm determined to solve it.

586
00:41:11,813 --> 00:41:14,605
I'll definitely give the
answer to your question.

587
00:41:16,938 --> 00:41:17,938
It's my promise.

588
00:41:21,813 --> 00:41:25,396
The day I give you the answer… will
you give me what I want in return?

589
00:41:25,771 --> 00:41:26,688
Yes.

590
00:41:31,813 --> 00:41:34,480
He spent four days near the
temple that Vikranth used to visit.

591
00:41:37,105 --> 00:41:39,855
But he spent a month at the
temple that Achyuth's used to visit.

592
00:41:42,771 --> 00:41:44,480
He took a lot of time to kill Achyuth.

593
00:41:48,188 --> 00:41:49,855
But he didn't spend that
much time in Vikranth's case.

594
00:41:50,021 --> 00:41:51,021
Why?

595
00:41:53,521 --> 00:41:55,480
Vikranth is an important
witness in a big case.

596
00:41:56,021 --> 00:41:58,771
But Achyuth is a man who
didn't mess with anyone.

597
00:42:00,605 --> 00:42:02,063
Anjali was his world.

598
00:42:07,730 --> 00:42:11,021
Who could possibly benefit from his death?

599
00:42:22,438 --> 00:42:24,271
Achyuth and Vikranth have
some connection, dude.

600
00:42:38,855 --> 00:42:41,855
- Boss, it's done. Take a look at it.
- Very good!

601
00:42:41,938 --> 00:42:46,063
'Forever in your memories. All… but'

602
00:42:46,813 --> 00:42:48,480
Anji, hold it once.

603
00:42:49,396 --> 00:42:50,563
{\an8}You are so dead, you idiot.

604
00:42:50,646 --> 00:42:52,688
{\an8}- Boss! Boss!
- Leave him, uncle. He's just a kid.

605
00:42:52,771 --> 00:42:54,688
{\an8}- Leave me, boss!
- Let you go?

606
00:42:54,771 --> 00:42:56,396
{\an8}- Isn't it good?
- Did you see what he wrote?

607
00:42:56,605 --> 00:42:59,646
The name they gave was gave Albert,
but he wrote 'All but'.

608
00:42:59,771 --> 00:43:01,438
- Sorry, Boss…
- He ruined the slate!

609
00:43:01,646 --> 00:43:03,521
- How many times did I tell you?
- You did, boss!

610
00:43:03,605 --> 00:43:05,521
I told you to practice on paper first.

611
00:43:05,605 --> 00:43:07,313
You have only one chance on the stone.

612
00:43:09,730 --> 00:43:12,980
Didn't I tell you to practice
and make it perfect?

613
00:43:18,855 --> 00:43:19,771
Get lost!

614
00:43:19,938 --> 00:43:21,063
Useless!

615
00:43:21,146 --> 00:43:22,938
Uncle, he is practicing.

616
00:43:23,313 --> 00:43:24,313
What?

617
00:43:24,688 --> 00:43:25,980
He is practicing, uncle.

618
00:43:26,105 --> 00:43:28,438
Are you out of your mind? What practice?

619
00:43:28,563 --> 00:43:30,521
Vikranth was the prime
witness in the BBA case.

620
00:43:30,605 --> 00:43:32,313
He always has
plainclothes cops around him.

621
00:43:32,938 --> 00:43:35,688
If his plan to stage an
accident for Vikranth fails…

622
00:43:36,146 --> 00:43:37,896
He knew the cops would
be alerted immediately.

623
00:43:38,146 --> 00:43:39,230
He couldn't afford to take such risk.

624
00:43:39,896 --> 00:43:41,355
He has only one chance.

625
00:43:41,438 --> 00:43:42,313
So?

626
00:43:42,563 --> 00:43:44,396
That's why he identified Achyuth.

627
00:43:44,855 --> 00:43:46,230
He used him for practice.

628
00:43:51,605 --> 00:43:53,896
Why would he kill Achyuth
in order to kill someone else?

629
00:43:54,521 --> 00:43:56,105
Both have the same daily routine.

630
00:43:56,188 --> 00:43:57,605
How can that be, Jay?

631
00:43:58,771 --> 00:44:01,646
Both of them used to stop at a
temple during their morning jogs.

632
00:44:03,855 --> 00:44:04,813
How do you know?

633
00:44:04,938 --> 00:44:06,313
That's where both of them died, right?

634
00:44:06,396 --> 00:44:08,521
But only the temple matches in both cases!

635
00:44:09,438 --> 00:44:10,646
Not only the temple, uncle.

636
00:44:11,688 --> 00:44:13,146
'He brushed it off,
saying he can always take the Metro.'

637
00:44:14,980 --> 00:44:18,688
'After the Metro started, we became
close friends while traveling together.'

638
00:44:21,021 --> 00:44:23,855
'Our spiritual gathering is full
from 6 pm to 7 pm everyday.'

639
00:44:24,146 --> 00:44:25,646
'He used to play for an hour every day.'

640
00:44:33,313 --> 00:44:34,896
He followed Achyuth for a month.

641
00:44:35,188 --> 00:44:36,938
He tried to kill him twice.

642
00:44:37,021 --> 00:44:38,063
But his attempts failed.

643
00:44:38,646 --> 00:44:40,230
He was successful in his third attempt.

644
00:44:40,605 --> 00:44:43,146
He implemented the
successful plan on Vikranth.

645
00:44:47,896 --> 00:44:49,396
Before giving a medicine to a person,

646
00:44:49,521 --> 00:44:53,021
to know whether it works
or not, it is tested on rats.

647
00:44:53,646 --> 00:44:56,563
Many rats meet their end
during that experiment.

648
00:44:57,188 --> 00:45:00,396
The poor rats don't
even know why they die.

649
00:45:01,105 --> 00:45:02,146
Like Mr. Achyuth.

650
00:45:02,521 --> 00:45:04,521
Will you tell all this to Anjali then?

651
00:45:06,730 --> 00:45:08,146
What do I tell Anjali?

652
00:45:08,855 --> 00:45:11,021
It is difficult even for us to understand.

653
00:45:13,230 --> 00:45:14,230
She is just a kid.

654
00:45:46,980 --> 00:45:47,980
Jai hind, sir.

655
00:45:48,771 --> 00:45:51,188
{\an8}- How far has the investigation come?
- It is going on, sir.

656
00:45:51,521 --> 00:45:53,355
{\an8}- Anything from the inquiry?
- No, sir.

657
00:45:53,730 --> 00:45:56,230
{\an8}In the CCTV camera footage or forensic?

658
00:45:57,438 --> 00:45:59,105
I'll tell you. Nothing.

659
00:46:01,063 --> 00:46:03,188
They are pestering me to close the case.

660
00:46:04,146 --> 00:46:06,771
It was just a simple open and shut case

661
00:46:06,896 --> 00:46:09,855
until you opened your stupid
mouth in front of the media.

662
00:46:10,105 --> 00:46:12,396
{\an8}Media people are coming
in another 30 minutes.

663
00:46:13,355 --> 00:46:14,938
{\an8}It was just an accident.

664
00:46:15,438 --> 00:46:16,813
We are closing the case.

665
00:46:17,438 --> 00:46:20,063
{\an8}Tell them you're sorry for
creating such confusion.

666
00:46:21,021 --> 00:46:23,271
Not a single word to be missed.

667
00:46:30,938 --> 00:46:31,855
Where are you?

668
00:46:31,938 --> 00:46:33,896
On the terrace of Swan Lake Apartments.

669
00:46:34,021 --> 00:46:35,230
What are you doing there?

670
00:46:35,396 --> 00:46:37,230
Is it a new customer or
someone about to die?

671
00:46:37,313 --> 00:46:40,146
The killer has been watching
Mr. Achyuth for almost a month.

672
00:46:41,480 --> 00:46:42,730
I know. You told me.

673
00:46:42,813 --> 00:46:44,605
Would you find a clue if
you say it many times?

674
00:46:44,688 --> 00:46:45,563
I got it.

675
00:46:49,355 --> 00:46:52,938
<i>In order to know Achyuth's</i>
<i>day to day activities…</i>

676
00:46:53,230 --> 00:46:55,438
<i>he should be continuously</i>
<i>watching Achyuth's house.</i>

677
00:46:55,855 --> 00:46:58,563
Swan Lake Apartments are
opposite Achyuth's house.

678
00:47:00,021 --> 00:47:02,271
<i>One of its towers is</i>
<i>facing Achyuth's house.</i>

679
00:47:02,355 --> 00:47:04,188
So there's a chance the
killer watched him from here.

680
00:47:25,355 --> 00:47:27,021
<i>How will you find out even then?</i>

681
00:47:27,355 --> 00:47:28,271
I will find it.

682
00:47:30,771 --> 00:47:34,021
Aunty, did you see a bald
man wearing powered glasses…

683
00:47:34,105 --> 00:47:36,313
- and leg affected by polio?
- I didn't.

684
00:47:36,980 --> 00:47:38,271
- You didn't?
- No.

685
00:47:39,188 --> 00:47:41,730
Madam, how's the enquiry
progressing? Any updates?

686
00:47:42,355 --> 00:47:43,313
<i>Did you nab the killer?</i>

687
00:47:43,396 --> 00:47:45,188
<i>Was Vikranth murdered or not?</i>

688
00:47:47,021 --> 00:47:50,146
Did you see a bald man
wearing powered glasses…

689
00:47:50,230 --> 00:47:53,563
- and leg affected by polio?
- No, sir.

690
00:47:53,813 --> 00:47:55,230
We investigated thoroughly.

691
00:47:55,688 --> 00:47:57,271
We left no stone unturned.

692
00:47:57,355 --> 00:47:59,188
We did not find any foul play.

693
00:48:00,355 --> 00:48:01,230
- Hello, sir.
- Hello…

694
00:48:01,313 --> 00:48:06,146
Did you see a bald man
wearing powered glasses…

695
00:48:06,271 --> 00:48:08,480
and leg affected by polio?

696
00:48:10,605 --> 00:48:11,896
Did you such a man around?

697
00:48:12,146 --> 00:48:15,605
It was just an unfortunate accident
that happened to Mr. Vikranth.

698
00:48:16,396 --> 00:48:20,730
Also, for any confusion created,
my sincere apologies.

699
00:48:42,230 --> 00:48:43,938
- Yes?
- One minute, brother.

700
00:48:44,771 --> 00:48:46,063
I've climbed way too
many stairs just now.

701
00:48:51,938 --> 00:48:55,063
A bald headed man… with thick,
high-powered glasses over his eyes.

702
00:48:56,563 --> 00:48:57,563
Polio-affected left leg.

703
00:48:59,605 --> 00:49:00,896
Did you see such a person around?

704
00:49:06,438 --> 00:49:07,355
Did you notice someone?

705
00:49:10,063 --> 00:49:10,980
No.

706
00:49:11,313 --> 00:49:12,188
You didn't?

707
00:50:04,730 --> 00:50:06,646
- Please recollect if you have seen him.
- No.

708
00:50:24,896 --> 00:50:26,438
Those plants are placed in the way.

709
00:50:26,521 --> 00:50:27,521
Ask them to remove them.

710
00:50:31,855 --> 00:50:34,355
A bald headed man… with thick,
high-powered glasses over his eyes.

711
00:50:34,438 --> 00:50:36,313
- Can't hear you.
- Can't you hear me?

712
00:50:36,438 --> 00:50:38,355
Polio-affected left leg.

713
00:50:38,438 --> 00:50:41,230
He is tall, I mean good height.

714
00:54:36,980 --> 00:54:38,938
- Yes, Sadhu.
- Bashir…

715
00:54:39,021 --> 00:54:42,438
I want the incoming call details
from every cell tower in my area.

716
00:54:43,438 --> 00:54:45,521
Do you want the details
from any specific time?

717
00:54:45,605 --> 00:54:47,021
{\an8}♪ Vow… My vow… ♪

718
00:54:47,105 --> 00:54:51,188
{\an8}- From 9:36 am to 10:42 am.
- ♪ Your end is my vow. ♪

719
00:54:51,313 --> 00:54:53,730
♪ Vow… My vow… ♪

720
00:54:53,855 --> 00:54:57,355
♪ Your end is my vow. ♪

721
00:54:58,438 --> 00:54:59,938
- Who is this?
- Whom do you want to talk to?

722
00:55:01,855 --> 00:55:02,855
Wait… wait…

723
00:55:03,271 --> 00:55:05,855
{\an8}A bald headed man- with thick,
high-powered glasses over his eyes.

724
00:55:06,271 --> 00:55:07,313
Polio-affected left leg.

725
00:55:07,396 --> 00:55:08,563
Did you see such a person around?

726
00:55:10,230 --> 00:55:12,063
His name is Mrityunjay.

727
00:55:13,355 --> 00:55:15,313
People call him Jay.

728
00:55:16,605 --> 00:55:18,646
{\an8}Sahara colony Block 8.

729
00:55:18,730 --> 00:55:19,771
Flat number 302.

730
00:55:20,063 --> 00:55:23,355
He collects obituary ads
for the Swechha newspaper.

731
00:55:27,396 --> 00:55:29,480
♪ Vow… My vow… ♪

732
00:55:29,980 --> 00:55:33,396
♪ Your end is my vow. ♪

733
00:55:45,313 --> 00:55:47,188
Why didn't you stop it back there? Fool!

734
00:55:47,271 --> 00:55:49,230
Applied brakes back there,
stopped on its own terms!

735
00:55:50,396 --> 00:55:51,563
We can track Jay's phone.

736
00:55:51,646 --> 00:55:53,563
But not like a GPS tracker.

737
00:55:53,646 --> 00:55:54,980
Cell tower to cell tower.

738
00:55:55,063 --> 00:55:56,813
I would only know the area he is in.

739
00:55:57,021 --> 00:55:59,188
His location details
will come to your app.

740
00:56:05,355 --> 00:56:09,021
<i>Among thousands of men,</i>
<i>one may strive for perfection.</i>

741
00:56:09,605 --> 00:56:11,063
Hey, rewind that.

742
00:56:11,438 --> 00:56:12,563
- What happened?
- Rewind it.

743
00:56:14,021 --> 00:56:15,563
<i>- Among thousands of men…</i>
- But why?

744
00:56:15,855 --> 00:56:17,563
<i>one may strive for perfection.</i>

745
00:56:17,896 --> 00:56:19,646
- He is a perfectionist.
- What?

746
00:56:19,938 --> 00:56:22,813
If he's doing it this perfectly,
these aren't his first murders.

747
00:56:22,896 --> 00:56:23,771
Turn back!

748
00:56:23,855 --> 00:56:26,313
{\an8}I'm telling you there's no one, but you
insist he's committed many murders.

749
00:56:26,396 --> 00:56:27,730
How can a non-existent person
commit murders?

750
00:56:27,813 --> 00:56:29,896
Satthi, not just natural deaths,

751
00:56:29,980 --> 00:56:32,480
any death in the city
comes to you for postmortem.

752
00:56:32,563 --> 00:56:34,855
- So?
- I need those records and details.

753
00:56:34,938 --> 00:56:35,896
Are you kidding?

754
00:56:35,980 --> 00:56:38,063
If the files are exposed,
I'll be the next body on the table.

755
00:56:40,355 --> 00:56:42,480
Hey, you can send Jay inside.

756
00:56:50,688 --> 00:56:53,188
The doctor will conduct three postmortem
and then go to lunch.

757
00:56:53,271 --> 00:56:54,605
You have one hour at most.

758
00:56:54,688 --> 00:56:56,438
What? Three postmortems in an hour?

759
00:56:56,521 --> 00:56:58,980
Is he planning to revive the dead
by operating so carefully?

760
00:56:59,396 --> 00:57:01,521
- Oh, okay. You're right.
- That's enough time.

761
00:57:01,896 --> 00:57:03,355
Hey, you park the van and come.

762
00:57:03,688 --> 00:57:05,188
- You come with me.
- Alright.

763
00:57:14,271 --> 00:57:15,230
GOVERNMENT HOSPITAL

764
00:57:17,646 --> 00:57:20,313
This is the first time I'm taking
such a risk. Do you get it?

765
00:57:20,396 --> 00:57:21,355
Greetings, sir.

766
00:57:21,438 --> 00:57:23,313
- Well…
- Oh no! The doctor!

767
00:57:23,396 --> 00:57:24,563
Why did you turn around?

768
00:57:24,646 --> 00:57:27,771
Seeing him felt like being
watched by an exam invigilator.

769
00:57:27,855 --> 00:57:29,938
- So?
- They tend to catch students who cheat.

770
00:57:30,730 --> 00:57:33,730
Hey, he's a doctor.
Don't blurt out things without thinking!

771
00:57:34,438 --> 00:57:36,188
- Be a man!
- You sure?

772
00:57:36,355 --> 00:57:37,271
Hmm.

773
00:57:49,646 --> 00:57:51,688
- My hands are shivering, dude.
- Quit alcohol then.

774
00:57:53,355 --> 00:57:54,313
- Jay…
- Huh?

775
00:57:54,730 --> 00:57:55,896
You just have half an hour.

776
00:57:56,105 --> 00:57:57,313
- That's enough.
- Hmm.

777
00:57:59,646 --> 00:58:00,730
- Satthi?
- Ah?

778
00:58:02,313 --> 00:58:06,063
- Why is that record room open?
- Well…

779
00:58:06,146 --> 00:58:09,313
- Did you put my lunch box inside?
- Yes, sir.

780
00:58:09,396 --> 00:58:10,271
Thanks, sir.

781
00:58:10,355 --> 00:58:12,605
Fine, lock the door.
Come with me. I need your help.

782
00:58:12,688 --> 00:58:13,563
Okay, sir.

783
00:58:18,771 --> 00:58:19,646
Sir.

784
00:58:39,271 --> 00:58:42,188
{\an8}I've ran all the medical tests. Only one
person survived after using the medicines.

785
00:58:42,855 --> 00:58:43,771
Satthi!

786
00:58:43,855 --> 00:58:45,646
Hey, stay there. I am coming.

787
00:58:46,730 --> 00:58:47,730
What is he saying?

788
00:58:48,146 --> 00:58:49,021
What is it, man?

789
00:58:49,813 --> 00:58:50,771
You idiot!

790
00:58:52,688 --> 00:58:53,813
The room is locked.

791
00:58:54,146 --> 00:58:55,730
Oh, about the van?

792
00:58:55,813 --> 00:58:57,980
I parked it, you don't worry.

793
00:58:59,646 --> 00:59:00,730
Keys, man. Keys.

794
00:59:03,188 --> 00:59:04,188
Even I have keys.

795
01:00:04,063 --> 01:00:05,730
<i>- Jay, we have a new case.</i>
- I'm on an important task.

796
01:00:05,813 --> 01:00:07,188
<i>- But I gave my word.</i>
- I can't.

797
01:00:10,605 --> 01:00:11,813
<i>- Please, dude.</i>
- Alright, I'll do it.

798
01:00:55,521 --> 01:00:58,313
Sadhu! I don't know what you're doing.

799
01:00:58,980 --> 01:01:02,021
But the Sadhu I know
never loses his focus.

800
01:01:02,438 --> 01:01:05,563
He is fully focused on his work.

801
01:01:12,230 --> 01:01:15,271
♪ Always on the hunt. ♪

802
01:01:18,230 --> 01:01:21,313
♪ It's all a gamble. ♪

803
01:01:23,480 --> 01:01:26,938
♪ My blood is vicious! ♪

804
01:01:29,480 --> 01:01:32,896
♪ It's all my anger totally. ♪

805
01:01:38,521 --> 01:01:39,396
Where are we headed now?

806
01:01:39,480 --> 01:01:41,521
Head to the 7D Coffee
Shop. Madam's there.

807
01:01:42,563 --> 01:01:44,896
♪ Vow… My vow… ♪

808
01:01:45,146 --> 01:01:48,688
♪ Your end is my vow. ♪

809
01:01:48,771 --> 01:01:49,896
Who's this now?

810
01:01:50,355 --> 01:01:52,146
- Who is on the phone?
- It is Satthi.

811
01:01:52,230 --> 01:01:54,438
- Hey, cut it…
- Why? What happened?

812
01:01:55,271 --> 01:01:57,355
He is very angry with you.

813
01:01:57,480 --> 01:01:58,355
Why?

814
01:01:58,521 --> 01:02:00,813
I escaped without
getting caught by the doctors.

815
01:02:01,105 --> 01:02:02,146
Escaped?

816
01:02:02,230 --> 01:02:04,438
You made an exit like
Hanuman exited from Lanka.

817
01:02:04,605 --> 01:02:05,646
You broke the doors.

818
01:02:05,730 --> 01:02:07,896
You broke the mirrors
and pushed the cupboards.

819
01:02:09,480 --> 01:02:11,646
Someone saw two men
leaving from the window.

820
01:02:11,813 --> 01:02:13,980
Someone else broke
the locks in the hospital.

821
01:02:14,063 --> 01:02:15,980
All the blame fell on Satthi.

822
01:02:16,521 --> 01:02:18,813
If you get caught by him,
he would kill you.

823
01:02:18,896 --> 01:02:20,313
Oh no! Then I won't answer his call.

824
01:02:20,396 --> 01:02:22,688
How do you know Madam's location?

825
01:02:22,771 --> 01:02:24,146
I made a call pretending
to be from the CM chamber

826
01:02:24,230 --> 01:02:25,438
they told me where madam is.

827
01:02:25,521 --> 01:02:27,771
Why don't you use this
smartness on your editor?

828
01:02:34,771 --> 01:02:35,646
Park it.

829
01:02:35,771 --> 01:02:37,605
This restaurant owner's
father is our customer.

830
01:02:37,896 --> 01:02:40,480
I usually visit only in five-star hotels.

831
01:02:40,771 --> 01:02:41,980
It's not that I like the taste.

832
01:02:42,063 --> 01:02:43,688
It's just that I prefer class, you see.

833
01:02:44,230 --> 01:02:47,896
It's not good for an IAS officer to
be seen in a small hotel like this.

834
01:02:49,688 --> 01:02:50,730
Don't get me wrong.

835
01:02:50,980 --> 01:02:52,855
If where I eat is this important,

836
01:02:52,938 --> 01:02:55,605
imagine how much more
important who I marry is.

837
01:02:56,646 --> 01:02:57,605
Hmm!

838
01:02:58,230 --> 01:03:00,105
Our madam is inside, she called us in.

839
01:03:23,980 --> 01:03:24,896
Madam, you're here?

840
01:03:24,980 --> 01:03:26,855
I didn't recognize you as
you're dressed in a saree.

841
01:03:26,938 --> 01:03:27,980
I need to talk to you urgently.

842
01:03:28,063 --> 01:03:29,896
Not here. Come to the office. Let's talk.

843
01:03:29,980 --> 01:03:31,313
Yeah, this is our personal space.

844
01:03:31,563 --> 01:03:33,313
What's personal when
someone is dying, sir.

845
01:03:33,605 --> 01:03:35,605
Jay, not now. Later.

846
01:03:35,813 --> 01:03:36,855
Madam, please listen to me…

847
01:03:36,938 --> 01:03:39,396
This isn't the place or
time to talk about the case.

848
01:03:39,563 --> 01:03:40,438
- Madam.
- Please leave.

849
01:03:40,521 --> 01:03:41,855
Both deaths were definitely murders.

850
01:03:42,563 --> 01:03:43,438
Not just that…

851
01:03:43,521 --> 01:03:47,105
On Jan 26th, our Malkajgiri
Corporator died in an accident.

852
01:03:47,188 --> 01:03:48,646
Exactly one week ago,

853
01:03:48,896 --> 01:03:53,188
The PA of the man who ran
against him also died in an accident.

854
01:03:53,605 --> 01:03:55,313
Jay, can you please stop this nonsense?

855
01:03:55,396 --> 01:03:59,355
On Jan 23rd, a software company
MD died near Raheja Mindspace.

856
01:03:59,521 --> 01:04:01,855
Exactly one week ago,
in the same building,

857
01:04:01,980 --> 01:04:06,313
An HR from another software company
also died in exactly the same way, madam.

858
01:04:06,396 --> 01:04:08,521
I'm certain, madam. These are all murders.

859
01:04:13,146 --> 01:04:14,105
Jay…

860
01:04:14,188 --> 01:04:15,563
This is an accident.

861
01:04:15,938 --> 01:04:18,396
- Nothing more than that.
- Please, madam. Believe me.

862
01:04:18,605 --> 01:04:19,605
Constable.

863
01:04:19,896 --> 01:04:22,605
- Madam, if everything is clear…
- Take him out.

864
01:04:23,105 --> 01:04:24,355
Hey, let's go.

865
01:04:24,938 --> 01:04:26,396
- Please, uncle…
- Let's go.

866
01:04:27,646 --> 01:04:29,355
Don't try to be a hero, Jay.

867
01:04:43,105 --> 01:04:44,730
Why should I try to be a hero, madam?

868
01:04:46,438 --> 01:04:47,313
I'm already a hero!

869
01:04:51,980 --> 01:04:57,063
The day that girl held my hand…

870
01:05:03,480 --> 01:05:05,396
That's when she made me a hero, madam.

871
01:05:09,188 --> 01:05:12,063
This hero promised to tell
her what happened to her dad.

872
01:05:15,188 --> 01:05:16,771
But the problem here is…

873
01:05:18,480 --> 01:05:21,563
This hero is unable to
figure out who the villain is.

874
01:05:27,188 --> 01:05:28,855
Anjali believes that a villain exists.

875
01:05:30,813 --> 01:05:32,105
And I trust her instincts.

876
01:05:38,771 --> 01:05:40,813
I have to restore her lost confidence.

877
01:05:43,105 --> 01:05:45,063
I have to see Anjali smiling again.

878
01:05:52,563 --> 01:05:53,896
No matter what anyone thinks…

879
01:05:55,563 --> 01:05:56,688
I'll nab him.

880
01:06:00,563 --> 01:06:01,563
Let's go, uncle.

881
01:06:18,188 --> 01:06:21,021
Alright, let's assume that
there is someone like you said.

882
01:06:21,271 --> 01:06:25,063
If he's roaming around without getting
caught, he must be very smart, right?

883
01:06:25,146 --> 01:06:26,188
He is, uncle!

884
01:06:26,271 --> 01:06:27,813
If he is so smart,

885
01:06:27,896 --> 01:06:30,313
he should have killed you
before you discovered him!

886
01:06:31,230 --> 01:06:32,313
He should have, uncle.

887
01:06:32,438 --> 01:06:34,063
But he doesn't know that I exist, right?

888
01:06:50,146 --> 01:06:53,688
There is nothing in
this world as purifying as wisdom.

889
01:06:56,771 --> 01:06:57,771
I will call you.

890
01:07:21,021 --> 01:07:22,563
'If he is so smart,'

891
01:07:22,646 --> 01:07:25,021
'he should have killed you
before you discovered him!'

892
01:07:25,105 --> 01:07:27,105
'Someone saw two men
leaving through the window.'

893
01:07:27,188 --> 01:07:29,271
'Someone else broke
the locks in the hospital.'

894
01:09:02,730 --> 01:09:03,605
Come on.

895
01:09:07,438 --> 01:09:08,438
Hey, you!

896
01:09:08,563 --> 01:09:10,688
- What are you doing?!
- How could you hit a policeman?!

897
01:09:14,896 --> 01:09:16,521
What did he do that you hit him?

898
01:09:17,230 --> 01:09:18,105
Are you out of your mind?

899
01:09:18,188 --> 01:09:19,355
You seem like an educated guy!

900
01:09:19,480 --> 01:09:20,521
Why are you acting like a thug?

901
01:09:22,480 --> 01:09:24,271
We're talking to you.
Why won't you say anything?

902
01:09:24,355 --> 01:09:25,313
How dare you hit a cop?

903
01:09:26,271 --> 01:09:27,480
Hey, get out of the way!

904
01:09:53,480 --> 01:09:54,521
Seems tough.

905
01:09:54,688 --> 01:09:56,771
- I expected the case to end that day.
- Didn't happen.

906
01:09:56,855 --> 01:09:57,855
- Hey, Suri.
- Yes, brother?

907
01:09:57,938 --> 01:09:59,438
- Is he the one who slapped our friend?
- Yes, brother.

908
01:09:59,521 --> 01:10:01,480
- How many days did the judge sentence him?
- Ten days, brother.

909
01:10:13,980 --> 01:10:19,896
♪ A great danger is lurking. ♪

910
01:10:21,938 --> 01:10:27,896
♪ It's crossing the ♪
♪ boundaries of your safety. ♪

911
01:10:29,980 --> 01:10:34,688
♪ Like a shadow, ♪
♪ the shocking danger crawls silently. ♪

912
01:10:54,021 --> 01:11:00,063
♪ Brute force has ♪
♪ weakened before iron will. ♪

913
01:11:02,021 --> 01:11:07,730
♪ I've decided that ♪
♪ your doom is certain. ♪

914
01:11:07,813 --> 01:11:09,730
- Nallabelli Harsha!
- Yes, sir!

915
01:11:10,021 --> 01:11:11,063
♪ Mrityunjaya! ♪

916
01:11:11,146 --> 01:11:12,021
Yes, sir!

917
01:11:12,105 --> 01:11:13,980
- ♪ Mrityunjaya! ♪
- Sameer!

918
01:11:14,063 --> 01:11:17,896
♪ Life is on the swing of doom! ♪

919
01:11:17,980 --> 01:11:19,396
♪ Mrityunjaya! ♪

920
01:11:20,021 --> 01:11:21,355
♪ Mrityunjaya! ♪

921
01:11:21,980 --> 01:11:26,230
♪ The enemy has set his trap. ♪

922
01:11:27,896 --> 01:11:28,980
Fear.

923
01:11:29,396 --> 01:11:30,980
Such a powerful emotion.

924
01:11:31,771 --> 01:11:36,938
99 out of 100 decisions we
take in life depend on our fear.

925
01:11:37,188 --> 01:11:39,646
But once we overcome that fear,

926
01:11:50,146 --> 01:11:51,771
our victory begins.

927
01:11:56,938 --> 01:12:01,230
I think a hundred times
before every step I take.

928
01:12:01,480 --> 01:12:03,355
But I made a mistake somewhere.

929
01:12:03,813 --> 01:12:05,396
I revealed myself to you.

930
01:12:05,813 --> 01:12:07,230
- How did you find me?
- How did you find me?

931
01:12:07,730 --> 01:12:09,438
You won't leave me without killing me.

932
01:12:09,688 --> 01:12:10,938
Will you come to prison?

933
01:12:11,396 --> 01:12:14,063
Or will you wait for my release?

934
01:12:14,521 --> 01:12:16,355
After you came out of the house,

935
01:12:16,771 --> 01:12:17,771
you could have boarded a bus.

936
01:12:18,271 --> 01:12:19,855
You might have boarded a van.

937
01:12:20,563 --> 01:12:22,105
But why did you go to prison?

938
01:12:22,605 --> 01:12:24,105
- What will you do next?
- What will you do next?

939
01:12:27,146 --> 01:12:28,355
- Whatever you do,
- Whatever you do,

940
01:12:28,605 --> 01:12:30,230
- You can't escape me.
- You can't escape me.

941
01:12:52,188 --> 01:12:53,771
Someone is trying to kill me.

942
01:12:55,730 --> 01:12:56,938
Why are you telling that to me?

943
01:12:57,771 --> 01:12:59,230
He is also a contract killer like you.

944
01:13:03,146 --> 01:13:04,521
I don't have any other option.

945
01:13:08,938 --> 01:13:10,563
You might have killed many people.

946
01:13:11,688 --> 01:13:13,313
But for the first time in your life,

947
01:13:13,396 --> 01:13:15,480
you got a chance to save lives.

948
01:13:15,771 --> 01:13:17,730
You got a chance to forgive yourself.

949
01:13:18,105 --> 01:13:19,146
Think about it.

950
01:13:21,188 --> 01:13:23,105
I need to know who
those contract killers are.

951
01:13:23,313 --> 01:13:25,980
How they work, how they think.

952
01:13:26,188 --> 01:13:27,105
Everything.

953
01:13:27,605 --> 01:13:29,313
Not everyone works the same way.

954
01:13:30,063 --> 01:13:31,896
But all of them have two things in common.

955
01:13:33,396 --> 01:13:35,646
The first one is their identity.

956
01:13:36,813 --> 01:13:39,063
No one should know
anything about us.

957
01:13:42,563 --> 01:13:43,980
No one should know that we exist.

958
01:13:45,105 --> 01:13:47,563
If anyone discovers,

959
01:13:48,771 --> 01:13:51,480
that will be the last moment for them.

960
01:13:52,938 --> 01:13:55,480
How will they get the contracts
if no one knows they exist?

961
01:13:57,146 --> 01:13:59,438
You are not that innocent.

962
01:13:59,605 --> 01:14:00,855
We have a handler.

963
01:14:01,021 --> 01:14:02,605
He gets the contracts.

964
01:14:02,730 --> 01:14:04,688
He forwards the details to us.

965
01:14:14,771 --> 01:14:15,771
Come son.

966
01:14:17,230 --> 01:14:18,105
Here son.

967
01:14:18,188 --> 01:14:19,313
You know what to do, right?

968
01:14:19,563 --> 01:14:20,771
I know, Bashir Bhai.

969
01:14:20,855 --> 01:14:22,938
I will put it where I have to.

970
01:14:23,396 --> 01:14:24,521
Except him,

971
01:14:24,855 --> 01:14:26,855
no one should know who we are.

972
01:14:28,980 --> 01:14:31,563
It's that important
to protect our identity.

973
01:14:50,646 --> 01:14:52,438
The second one is our contract.

974
01:14:55,105 --> 01:14:58,771
If a client gave us a
contract to kill a person,

975
01:15:00,021 --> 01:15:02,313
the client's life is in danger.

976
01:15:02,396 --> 01:15:03,855
We got the contract.

977
01:15:04,105 --> 01:15:06,063
It will be at the location by evening.

978
01:15:06,605 --> 01:15:09,896
If I knew you were coming here,
I wouldn't have sent it there.

979
01:15:10,313 --> 01:15:12,438
It's OK. I will take it.

980
01:15:12,605 --> 01:15:14,938
If you miss the contract,

981
01:15:15,355 --> 01:15:16,271
I won't miss it.

982
01:15:18,313 --> 01:15:20,355
I won't let our reputation be tarnished.

983
01:15:22,646 --> 01:15:23,563
Thanks.

984
01:15:24,521 --> 01:15:25,438
Seetha speaking.

985
01:15:25,646 --> 01:15:26,605
Madam, I am Jay.

986
01:15:26,813 --> 01:15:29,313
<i>Madam, please listen to me.</i>
<i>Just spare a minute.</i>

987
01:15:29,771 --> 01:15:30,688
Tell me.

988
01:15:30,813 --> 01:15:33,563
Madam, there are handlers
behind the killers, right?

989
01:15:33,646 --> 01:15:35,646
{\an8}Even if the BBA bank
owners didn't call the killer,

990
01:15:35,730 --> 01:15:37,480
he would have called the handler.

991
01:15:37,646 --> 01:15:40,855
You said you were checking the
records in the car that day, right?

992
01:15:41,063 --> 01:15:42,105
Check it once again, madam.

993
01:15:42,188 --> 01:15:43,730
<i>The handler will definitely</i>
<i>present in one of those records.</i>

994
01:15:53,813 --> 01:15:55,021
I'm sorry, Bashir.

995
01:16:19,646 --> 01:16:20,688
Not only that, madam.

996
01:16:20,813 --> 01:16:22,355
That killer is trying to kill me.

997
01:16:24,313 --> 01:16:25,521
Send someone to my house, madam.

998
01:16:25,605 --> 01:16:26,646
<i>He has left the gas leaking.</i>

999
01:16:26,730 --> 01:16:27,980
<i>Please madam,</i>
<i>you will understand if you visit.</i>

1000
01:16:28,480 --> 01:16:30,313
Please, madam. Trust me for once, madam.

1001
01:16:33,188 --> 01:16:35,230
- I will check.
- Thank you, madam. Thank you.

1002
01:16:58,188 --> 01:17:00,855
{\an8}So, Jay was telling the truth.

1003
01:17:06,480 --> 01:17:09,188
There is a number of one Bashir,
a pawn shop owner in the call list.

1004
01:17:09,271 --> 01:17:11,396
But surprisingly,
he was found dead last night.

1005
01:17:11,521 --> 01:17:13,063
He is on to something, Vinod.

1006
01:17:13,563 --> 01:17:15,563
He is looking through something
that we aren't able to.

1007
01:17:21,688 --> 01:17:24,480
{\an8}- I think he deserves a shot.
- I agree on that, madam.

1008
01:17:26,813 --> 01:17:28,230
{\an8}Let's go to Bashir's crime scene.

1009
01:17:29,896 --> 01:17:31,188
Inform the local team.

1010
01:17:31,438 --> 01:17:33,355
And we will take Jay along as well.

1011
01:17:33,438 --> 01:17:34,855
Madam, Jay is in jail.

1012
01:17:35,771 --> 01:17:36,688
What?

1013
01:17:49,688 --> 01:17:51,563
I don't like the smile.

1014
01:17:52,355 --> 01:17:54,396
If I see it again,
you will go back inside.

1015
01:17:54,980 --> 01:17:55,980
Hop in.

1016
01:18:06,480 --> 01:18:07,813
<i>- Jai Hind, madam.</i>
<i>- Jai Hind.</i>

1017
01:18:08,813 --> 01:18:10,771
<i>- Did you get the postmortem report?</i>
<i>- Not yet, madam.</i>

1018
01:18:10,896 --> 01:18:12,188
<i>It could be cardiac arrest.</i>

1019
01:18:16,980 --> 01:18:18,438
Are there any CCTV cameras?

1020
01:18:18,521 --> 01:18:19,521
No, madam.

1021
01:18:23,980 --> 01:18:25,730
Madam, there is a missing stick note.

1022
01:18:28,438 --> 01:18:29,688
Only this page is missing, madam.

1023
01:18:31,980 --> 01:18:34,063
- Bashir died here, right?
- Yes, madam.

1024
01:18:34,146 --> 01:18:35,188
Body position?

1025
01:18:35,313 --> 01:18:37,521
Bashir died with his
hands on the chair, madam.

1026
01:18:46,355 --> 01:18:47,313
The missing piece, madam.

1027
01:19:00,146 --> 01:19:02,605
Madam, this murder must
have been about the contract.

1028
01:19:02,855 --> 01:19:04,355
Madam, if we go to Monda market
at six o'clock,

1029
01:19:04,438 --> 01:19:06,271
we will definitely know
something about the killer.

1030
01:19:06,355 --> 01:19:07,646
It's already 3:30 pm.

1031
01:19:07,980 --> 01:19:09,188
Believe me, madam.
Let's go, madam.

1032
01:19:09,271 --> 01:19:11,563
If he takes the contract,
another life will be lost.

1033
01:19:11,646 --> 01:19:12,521
- Vinod.
- Madam?

1034
01:19:12,605 --> 01:19:13,855
- Call for backup.
- OK, madam.

1035
01:19:13,938 --> 01:19:15,480
In civil dress, okay? Immediately.

1036
01:19:27,396 --> 01:19:29,146
Madam. Why did you stop the vehicle here?

1037
01:19:29,230 --> 01:19:30,521
Can't you see the no parking board?

1038
01:19:30,605 --> 01:19:31,605
Move the vehicle. Come on.

1039
01:19:32,938 --> 01:19:33,813
Sorry, madam.

1040
01:19:37,146 --> 01:19:38,313
Boys, move.

1041
01:19:40,980 --> 01:19:42,896
Jay, you are not safe here.

1042
01:19:43,021 --> 01:19:43,896
- Come with me.
- No, madam.

1043
01:19:43,980 --> 01:19:44,896
I'll stay here. Please.

1044
01:19:45,438 --> 01:19:48,063
What? He could kill you.

1045
01:19:48,146 --> 01:19:49,771
Then, you can catch him easily, madam.

1046
01:19:49,855 --> 01:19:50,730
Please.

1047
01:19:53,771 --> 01:19:54,646
Here.

1048
01:19:54,730 --> 01:19:56,188
- Please be careful.
- Okay!

1049
01:20:05,021 --> 01:20:06,230
The killer is bald.

1050
01:20:09,396 --> 01:20:10,355
He wears high-powered glasses.

1051
01:20:12,563 --> 01:20:13,646
He has polio on his left leg.

1052
01:20:16,438 --> 01:20:18,563
- Boys, are we clear?
- Clear ma'am.

1053
01:20:18,646 --> 01:20:20,146
- Keep your eyes sharp.
- OK, ma'am.

1054
01:20:20,230 --> 01:20:21,813
- I need him no matter what.
- Yes, madam.

1055
01:21:01,438 --> 01:21:02,980
He has glasses, but he isn't bald.

1056
01:21:03,521 --> 01:21:05,813
We can't find anyone matching
the description Jay gave us.

1057
01:21:12,813 --> 01:21:14,855
It isn't necessary to have all the
three identifications which Jay gave us.

1058
01:21:15,271 --> 01:21:17,938
Even if you find one,
take him into custody. Over.

1059
01:21:18,146 --> 01:21:19,021
OK, take it.

1060
01:21:21,271 --> 01:21:22,230
Who are you?

1061
01:21:46,188 --> 01:21:47,063
Sorry.

1062
01:21:47,563 --> 01:21:48,688
Nithin, open that camera.

1063
01:21:56,396 --> 01:21:57,396
That one?

1064
01:21:57,521 --> 01:21:59,021
Jay, it's 6:10.

1065
01:21:59,271 --> 01:22:00,188
He isn't here yet.

1066
01:22:00,271 --> 01:22:01,688
He will come for sure, madam.

1067
01:22:02,480 --> 01:22:03,396
He'll have to.

1068
01:22:16,938 --> 01:22:17,938
Do you have a lighter, bro?

1069
01:22:42,105 --> 01:22:43,021
Thanks.

1070
01:22:55,896 --> 01:22:57,438
- Ma'am, he is here.
- What?

1071
01:23:12,521 --> 01:23:13,896
Boys, were you able to find him?

1072
01:23:13,980 --> 01:23:15,438
No, ma'am. We are not able to find him.

1073
01:23:18,105 --> 01:23:20,063
We searched everywhere, madam.
We didn't find him anywhere.

1074
01:23:20,271 --> 01:23:22,021
Can you zoom that?
The one to it's side too.

1075
01:23:22,105 --> 01:23:23,271
- Zoom it a bit.
- Where is he, Jay?

1076
01:23:23,355 --> 01:23:24,563
Zoom the others too.

1077
01:23:24,646 --> 01:23:26,438
That camera.

1078
01:23:26,730 --> 01:23:28,105
Jay, stop wasting my time.

1079
01:23:28,646 --> 01:23:29,813
He is really here, madam.

1080
01:23:29,896 --> 01:23:32,480
He even gave me the lighter
with the date October 2nd on it.

1081
01:23:33,230 --> 01:23:34,188
What is that date?

1082
01:23:34,480 --> 01:23:36,480
October 2nd is the date when
I'd be released from prison.

1083
01:23:36,563 --> 01:23:38,646
- He is trying to kill me on the same day.
- What nonsense!

1084
01:23:38,771 --> 01:23:40,271
Please believe me, madam.

1085
01:23:40,521 --> 01:23:42,313
Brother, please open
the footage on the left.

1086
01:23:42,480 --> 01:23:43,396
Yeah.

1087
01:23:43,480 --> 01:23:46,063
Jay, we can't keep going
on like this any longer.

1088
01:23:48,021 --> 01:23:50,355
You are not in the camera to
believe what you are saying.

1089
01:23:53,355 --> 01:23:54,355
God!

1090
01:24:30,938 --> 01:24:32,396
<i>Jay, stop wasting my time!</i>

1091
01:24:41,021 --> 01:24:42,480
Where the hell is he, damn it?

1092
01:25:07,896 --> 01:25:11,271
<i>Uncle, why did this happen to my father?</i>

1093
01:25:40,188 --> 01:25:41,230
What happened, son?

1094
01:25:42,480 --> 01:25:44,396
Aunt, I'm scared that I might lose.

1095
01:25:50,271 --> 01:25:52,146
It's not wrong to lose, son.

1096
01:25:52,896 --> 01:25:56,730
But it's wrong not to fight
out of fear of losing.

1097
01:25:56,855 --> 01:25:58,896
You need to see your enemy
to fight, right?

1098
01:25:59,063 --> 01:26:01,021
Don't you see your enemy?

1099
01:26:02,021 --> 01:26:04,355
Or are you failing to see him?

1100
01:26:14,896 --> 01:26:18,313
I checked the CCTV footage
from Vikranth's crime scene as well.

1101
01:26:18,938 --> 01:26:20,646
There is no such person there either.

1102
01:26:20,730 --> 01:26:24,480
Does he even exist,
or are you both just chasing shadows?

1103
01:26:24,605 --> 01:26:27,063
You're not even in the camera footage.
How can you say that?

1104
01:26:30,271 --> 01:26:31,313
Thanks, Aunt.

1105
01:26:39,355 --> 01:26:40,896
- He will leave in 5 minutes.
- OK.

1106
01:26:40,980 --> 01:26:41,855
Thanks, bro.

1107
01:26:41,938 --> 01:26:43,188
Dude, everything is set.

1108
01:26:43,771 --> 01:26:44,855
Check where he is.

1109
01:26:47,813 --> 01:26:48,855
Can you find him?

1110
01:26:50,855 --> 01:26:52,188
I can see him for the first time.

1111
01:26:52,396 --> 01:26:53,438
In which camera?

1112
01:26:54,313 --> 01:26:55,271
In all the cameras.

1113
01:26:55,355 --> 01:26:57,396
We shouldn't look for
the one who got captured.

1114
01:26:57,605 --> 01:26:59,271
We should look for the one
who escaped the cameras.

1115
01:27:35,646 --> 01:27:36,730
It could be anyone.

1116
01:27:36,813 --> 01:27:37,980
He just wasn't caught by the cameras.

1117
01:27:38,646 --> 01:27:41,021
If he is not caught on a single
one camera, he could be anyone.

1118
01:27:41,271 --> 01:27:43,313
But what if he is not caught
on any of the cameras?

1119
01:27:50,855 --> 01:27:52,730
Is he the guy in the GHMC dress?

1120
01:27:53,313 --> 01:27:54,771
But there is no polio on his legs.

1121
01:27:55,105 --> 01:27:56,730
I don't think he has any baldness too.

1122
01:27:57,605 --> 01:27:59,521
We are watching what he
is allowing us to watch.

1123
01:28:08,438 --> 01:28:10,396
He has been covering
his traces so perfectly…

1124
01:28:10,605 --> 01:28:12,021
We might not be able to catch him ever.

1125
01:28:20,355 --> 01:28:21,980
What time did he cross the camera?

1126
01:28:22,896 --> 01:28:24,605
This one is at 5:24 pm, sir.

1127
01:28:24,688 --> 01:28:25,688
5:24 pm…

1128
01:28:25,771 --> 01:28:28,105
- And this one?
- This is at 5:27 pm.

1129
01:28:31,021 --> 01:28:32,355
Three minutes?

1130
01:28:34,271 --> 01:28:37,605
Three minutes… three minutes…
three minutes!

1131
01:28:42,105 --> 01:28:43,938
So he has already accepted the contract.

1132
01:28:50,813 --> 01:28:52,230
He is following the target.

1133
01:29:12,355 --> 01:29:14,605
Do you have CC cameras
at the market entrance?

1134
01:29:14,855 --> 01:29:16,438
- Yes, sir.
- Play them once.

1135
01:29:19,313 --> 01:29:21,188
Note down all the bike numbers you see.

1136
01:29:21,271 --> 01:29:22,188
Give me the notebook, bro.

1137
01:29:23,230 --> 01:29:24,230
Quick.

1138
01:29:24,313 --> 01:29:25,271
Note them down.

1139
01:29:25,813 --> 01:29:26,980
Why do we need those numbers?

1140
01:29:27,313 --> 01:29:30,813
You said that all the cameras
are under his control.

1141
01:29:31,021 --> 01:29:33,021
But one camera was not under his control.

1142
01:29:48,813 --> 01:29:50,063
We have noted down everything.

1143
01:29:50,146 --> 01:29:51,105
What do we do now?

1144
01:29:52,188 --> 01:29:53,063
Brother…

1145
01:29:53,396 --> 01:29:54,563
Open the e-challan site.

1146
01:29:58,896 --> 01:30:00,188
What to look for here?

1147
01:30:00,688 --> 01:30:02,396
Check if someone is wearing GHMC dress.

1148
01:30:05,521 --> 01:30:06,521
There he is!

1149
01:30:06,896 --> 01:30:08,271
But we can't see him clearly.

1150
01:30:08,605 --> 01:30:09,563
Show me another photo.

1151
01:30:10,021 --> 01:30:11,063
Look! There he is!

1152
01:30:13,355 --> 01:30:14,771
He has something in his hand.

1153
01:30:15,063 --> 01:30:16,105
{\an8}I think it is a bottle.

1154
01:30:20,105 --> 01:30:21,771
{\an8}He is doing something with that bottle.

1155
01:30:21,896 --> 01:30:22,896
{\an8}He is keeping it in his pocket.

1156
01:30:23,146 --> 01:30:24,855
He is coming forward.

1157
01:30:28,896 --> 01:30:30,021
We missed him!

1158
01:30:40,105 --> 01:30:41,271
What are you looking at?

1159
01:30:41,688 --> 01:30:43,813
A person can change any
number of disguises.

1160
01:30:43,980 --> 01:30:45,396
But he can't change three things.

1161
01:30:45,480 --> 01:30:46,521
First is his height.

1162
01:30:46,938 --> 01:30:48,271
The second is the way he sees.

1163
01:30:48,355 --> 01:30:49,521
Look at his eyes.

1164
01:30:49,605 --> 01:30:51,896
He looks like a hungry
tiger eyeing its prey.

1165
01:30:51,980 --> 01:30:53,605
The third is habits.

1166
01:30:53,855 --> 01:30:54,938
Mannerisms.

1167
01:30:55,021 --> 01:30:57,313
His face is not clear
in any of the photos.

1168
01:30:57,688 --> 01:30:58,980
It is in one video.

1169
01:30:59,813 --> 01:31:00,771
Where is it?

1170
01:31:03,105 --> 01:31:04,063
It is in my phone.

1171
01:31:09,271 --> 01:31:10,146
Huh!

1172
01:31:11,021 --> 01:31:11,980
This guy?

1173
01:31:19,438 --> 01:31:20,355
A bald headed man…

1174
01:31:20,563 --> 01:31:21,813
Polio-affected left leg.

1175
01:31:22,105 --> 01:31:23,563
Did you see such a person around?

1176
01:31:24,230 --> 01:31:25,230
No.

1177
01:31:28,855 --> 01:31:29,730
This is bullshit.

1178
01:31:30,105 --> 01:31:31,313
Madam, he is the killer.

1179
01:31:31,396 --> 01:31:32,271
Do you have proof?

1180
01:31:32,438 --> 01:31:33,771
Why is she talking like this?

1181
01:31:34,771 --> 01:31:37,480
Jay, if you take a photo
and say that he is the killer,

1182
01:31:37,855 --> 01:31:39,730
- how should I believe you?
- No, madam.

1183
01:31:39,813 --> 01:31:41,438
Two people are dying
because of his practice.

1184
01:31:41,521 --> 01:31:43,105
- Madam…
- Pho--

1185
01:31:43,771 --> 01:31:45,855
- What if he kills someone?
- She isn't believing it.

1186
01:31:45,938 --> 01:31:47,396
- Do you understand?
- What should I do?

1187
01:31:47,480 --> 01:31:49,021
How many more people
should die in his hands?

1188
01:31:53,938 --> 01:31:55,105
- Here, uncle.
- Give it to me.

1189
01:31:55,188 --> 01:31:56,063
You pour another for yourself.

1190
01:31:56,938 --> 01:31:58,605
Dude, its raw. Nothing mixed in it.

1191
01:31:58,688 --> 01:32:00,480
Where have you been since noon?
You didn't even answer my calls!

1192
01:32:03,188 --> 01:32:05,188
Hey, Jay! Everything is over.

1193
01:32:05,480 --> 01:32:06,438
How can it be over?

1194
01:32:07,146 --> 01:32:08,063
How can it be over?

1195
01:32:09,355 --> 01:32:12,230
Until I declare it over, it's not over.

1196
01:32:12,771 --> 01:32:13,646
I won't let it end.

1197
01:32:14,313 --> 01:32:16,480
So what do you think we should do now?

1198
01:32:18,646 --> 01:32:19,688
Let's kill him.

1199
01:32:26,230 --> 01:32:28,896
OBITUARY
L. SUYODHAN

1200
01:32:30,021 --> 01:32:30,896
What is this now?

1201
01:32:36,105 --> 01:32:39,771
His biggest courage is that no
one knows about his existence.

1202
01:32:40,063 --> 01:32:41,855
I'll let this world know about him.

1203
01:32:42,230 --> 01:32:43,271
Not just today,

1204
01:32:43,355 --> 01:32:46,438
his ad will be in every
newspaper until we find it.

1205
01:32:59,480 --> 01:33:01,063
{\an8}OBITUARY
L. SUYODHAN

1206
01:33:19,730 --> 01:33:21,646
Our goal is not just catching him.

1207
01:33:24,646 --> 01:33:26,938
But to stop him from killing
two more innocent persons.

1208
01:33:29,771 --> 01:33:30,938
OBITUARY
L. SUYODHAN

1209
01:33:49,063 --> 01:33:50,313
What do you want, Mr. Murthy?

1210
01:33:50,646 --> 01:33:52,688
Give him another chance, madam.

1211
01:33:55,521 --> 01:33:56,396
What…

1212
01:33:56,480 --> 01:33:57,813
Do you think we will get him?

1213
01:33:58,271 --> 01:33:59,938
Even today,

1214
01:34:00,021 --> 01:34:03,438
there are many people who don't do
anything without reading the newspaper.

1215
01:34:03,521 --> 01:34:04,771
At least one of them would identify him.

1216
01:34:05,688 --> 01:34:06,563
At least one will get him.

1217
01:34:09,396 --> 01:34:10,605
Grandpa, coffee.

1218
01:34:13,938 --> 01:34:15,021
What happened, grandpa?

1219
01:34:15,813 --> 01:34:18,938
There's this ad coming in the newspaper
since some days that this guy is dead.

1220
01:34:19,021 --> 01:34:19,938
So?

1221
01:34:20,230 --> 01:34:21,980
People die only once.

1222
01:34:22,813 --> 01:34:24,980
Why is he dying once a day?

1223
01:34:26,063 --> 01:34:27,188
Have your coffee first.

1224
01:34:44,521 --> 01:34:46,438
Hey, boy! Boy!

1225
01:35:02,563 --> 01:35:05,980
- Hello.
- You published that your relative is dead.

1226
01:35:06,063 --> 01:35:07,480
Is he really dead?

1227
01:35:07,730 --> 01:35:08,730
Why are you asking that?

1228
01:35:08,813 --> 01:35:10,605
I've seen a man who looks just like him.

1229
01:35:10,813 --> 01:35:11,896
He looks exactly like him.

1230
01:35:15,396 --> 01:35:16,605
Where is he?

1231
01:35:29,896 --> 01:35:31,771
I will give you one last chance, Jay.

1232
01:35:53,771 --> 01:35:54,938
Mr. Murthy! Mr. Murthy!

1233
01:35:59,146 --> 01:36:00,105
Stay here, okay?

1234
01:36:00,438 --> 01:36:01,313
Hey, send everyone to safety.

1235
01:36:01,646 --> 01:36:03,188
- Get inside.
- Go inside, move.

1236
01:36:03,271 --> 01:36:04,896
- Get inside.
- Hey, get inside.

1237
01:36:10,271 --> 01:36:12,105
Madam you go inside. Go inside.

1238
01:36:12,188 --> 01:36:13,313
- Get inside.
- Hey, go inside.

1239
01:36:13,396 --> 01:36:15,355
Vinod, send backup to
my location immediately.

1240
01:36:15,771 --> 01:36:17,396
The suspect is armed and dangerous.

1241
01:36:18,271 --> 01:36:20,396
Jay, take care of him.

1242
01:36:25,896 --> 01:36:27,521
A little backwards. Come on.

1243
01:36:30,563 --> 01:36:31,438
Easy.

1244
01:36:31,688 --> 01:36:33,355
- Hey, Satthi, get him in.
- Hurry up!

1245
01:36:45,188 --> 01:36:46,063
{\an8}Take cover.

1246
01:36:55,438 --> 01:36:56,396
Come here!

1247
01:37:15,271 --> 01:37:16,646
Boys, take positions.

1248
01:37:16,896 --> 01:37:17,938
Ma'am, in position.

1249
01:37:18,313 --> 01:37:20,396
- In position, ma'am.
- Yes, ma'am. In position.

1250
01:37:24,646 --> 01:37:26,855
Vinod, do you have eyes on the target?

1251
01:37:27,063 --> 01:37:28,771
Yes, ma'am.
I see him at the extreme right door.

1252
01:37:30,896 --> 01:37:33,188
Boys, fire at will.

1253
01:37:48,521 --> 01:37:49,938
Vinod, where the hell is he?

1254
01:37:50,146 --> 01:37:51,438
Moving towards my extreme left.

1255
01:37:53,146 --> 01:37:55,063
- Now?
- He is at the middle door, ma'am.

1256
01:37:55,355 --> 01:37:56,230
Now?

1257
01:37:57,771 --> 01:37:58,688
Ma'am, in the kitchen door.

1258
01:38:50,980 --> 01:38:51,855
Ma'am!

1259
01:39:21,063 --> 01:39:21,938
It's over, Jay.

1260
01:39:23,480 --> 01:39:24,896
So easily?

1261
01:40:19,271 --> 01:40:20,396
- Uncle!
- Huh?

1262
01:40:24,271 --> 01:40:27,188
Move, move!
Visiting hours are over. Leave. Go!

1263
01:40:27,813 --> 01:40:28,938
We are closing the gate.

1264
01:40:40,105 --> 01:40:41,605
I've been waiting for three days.

1265
01:40:42,646 --> 01:40:43,646
I can't wait any longer.

1266
01:40:44,771 --> 01:40:46,355
Enough of your sneaky walk.

1267
01:40:47,563 --> 01:40:48,480
Come!

1268
01:41:04,438 --> 01:41:05,438
Hi, Mrityunjay.

1269
01:41:07,355 --> 01:41:08,271
I like your name.

1270
01:41:11,480 --> 01:41:13,313
By the way, my name is Sadhu.

1271
01:41:14,521 --> 01:41:16,313
And it's an absolute
pleasure to meet you.

1272
01:41:17,855 --> 01:41:21,855
When no one believed my existence…
only you did.

1273
01:41:22,521 --> 01:41:25,230
Now everyone believes that I am dead.

1274
01:41:32,021 --> 01:41:33,188
But you didn't.

1275
01:41:35,480 --> 01:41:36,605
How did you figure it out?

1276
01:41:37,021 --> 01:41:38,021
Two mistakes.

1277
01:41:38,896 --> 01:41:40,480
If you had taken the shot
from inside the house,

1278
01:41:40,605 --> 01:41:43,646
the bullet would have hit the scooter's
headlight, not the tire below.

1279
01:41:45,021 --> 01:41:47,980
Sadhu can miss his aim
once, but not six times.

1280
01:41:51,021 --> 01:41:51,896
Smart!

1281
01:41:54,730 --> 01:41:56,480
You've seen what no one has seen, Jay.

1282
01:41:57,188 --> 01:42:00,021
You are a masterpiece.

1283
01:42:00,521 --> 01:42:01,396
Thanks.

1284
01:42:02,188 --> 01:42:04,063
I'm sure you liked the
gift I gave you too, right?

1285
01:42:04,438 --> 01:42:05,313
The newspaper ad.

1286
01:42:07,188 --> 01:42:08,313
I saw it right on the first day.

1287
01:42:09,605 --> 01:42:11,105
I wanted to kill you.

1288
01:42:11,521 --> 01:42:13,230
- But…
- But you can't.

1289
01:42:13,605 --> 01:42:15,980
Because you set October
2nd as the day to kill me.

1290
01:42:17,896 --> 01:42:18,771
Yes.

1291
01:42:19,813 --> 01:42:20,813
And that's today!

1292
01:42:47,021 --> 01:42:48,146
Nice setup, Jay!

1293
01:42:50,021 --> 01:42:51,063
Thanks, Sadhu.

1294
01:42:54,271 --> 01:42:56,480
You don't know how lucky you are, Jay.

1295
01:42:56,980 --> 01:42:59,938
You've slipped past
death by me many times.

1296
01:43:02,646 --> 01:43:04,605
Do you know where my luck started, Sadhu?

1297
01:43:05,563 --> 01:43:06,563
I am curious!

1298
01:43:07,980 --> 01:43:10,813
When I came to your house and
asked you about your own details,

1299
01:43:10,896 --> 01:43:14,563
if you hadn't followed me,
I wouldn't have found you.

1300
01:43:30,063 --> 01:43:32,188
♪ Vow… My vow… ♪

1301
01:43:32,480 --> 01:43:35,438
♪ Your end is my vow. ♪

1302
01:43:35,521 --> 01:43:37,438
♪ Vow… My vow… ♪

1303
01:43:37,730 --> 01:43:40,730
♪ Your end is my vow. ♪

1304
01:43:43,646 --> 01:43:46,438
♪ Always on the hunt. ♪

1305
01:43:48,771 --> 01:43:50,646
♪ It's all a gamble. ♪

1306
01:43:50,730 --> 01:43:52,271
This time, I won't miss, Jay.

1307
01:43:52,563 --> 01:43:54,563
Yes, Sadhu. Even I won't miss this time.

1308
01:43:54,646 --> 01:43:56,313
♪ Your end is my vow. ♪

1309
01:43:56,396 --> 01:43:58,480
♪ Vow… My vow… ♪

1310
01:43:58,563 --> 01:44:01,646
♪ Your end is my vow. ♪

1311
01:44:18,021 --> 01:44:20,355
Every person follows a set pattern.

1312
01:44:20,480 --> 01:44:23,271
They all fall into their own brackets.

1313
01:44:23,396 --> 01:44:25,105
But I don't understand…

1314
01:44:25,855 --> 01:44:26,980
…only your pattern, Jay.

1315
01:44:28,271 --> 01:44:30,021
I didn't find anyone like you.

1316
01:44:30,146 --> 01:44:31,688
But I found someone like me.

1317
01:44:32,438 --> 01:44:34,146
- Who is that?
- It's you.

1318
01:44:34,938 --> 01:44:37,105
We both use disguises as a part of work.

1319
01:44:37,563 --> 01:44:39,688
We both do our job very well.

1320
01:44:41,896 --> 01:44:43,355
We both deal with deaths.

1321
01:44:44,230 --> 01:44:45,730
The only small difference is…

1322
01:44:45,855 --> 01:44:49,063
You show up before death…
I arrive after.

1323
01:44:49,396 --> 01:44:50,855
You are very predictable, Sadhu.

1324
01:44:52,105 --> 01:44:53,813
That's why I found you so easily.

1325
01:45:50,688 --> 01:45:51,563
Uncle!

1326
01:46:28,938 --> 01:46:30,021
Well played, Jay!

1327
01:46:30,980 --> 01:46:34,146
You thought you could beat me…
in the game I created?

1328
01:46:38,730 --> 01:46:40,021
You made a shadow bleed.

1329
01:46:41,355 --> 01:46:42,355
I'll give you that.

1330
01:46:42,980 --> 01:46:45,271
Even though you knew
I would come to kill you,

1331
01:46:46,105 --> 01:46:47,480
why are you still here?

1332
01:46:47,688 --> 01:46:49,980
Because of you,
a little girl forgot what it means to cry.

1333
01:46:51,146 --> 01:46:52,563
I just wanted to remind her to cry.

1334
01:46:53,355 --> 01:46:54,230
I didn't understand.

1335
01:46:56,563 --> 01:46:58,188
But if it is you saying this…

1336
01:46:59,313 --> 01:47:00,813
There must be something.

1337
01:47:01,355 --> 01:47:02,271
So…

1338
01:47:02,980 --> 01:47:04,521
It's all over, Jay.

1339
01:47:04,730 --> 01:47:05,605
It's not.

1340
01:47:06,563 --> 01:47:09,105
Not until I say it's over.

1341
01:47:11,063 --> 01:47:15,021
Even though death is right in front
of you, you're saying it's not over.

1342
01:47:15,688 --> 01:47:17,146
I like your confidence, Jay.

1343
01:47:18,813 --> 01:47:19,896
Any last words?

1344
01:47:22,938 --> 01:47:25,396
There are three things a person
can never change about themselves.

1345
01:47:26,271 --> 01:47:27,813
First is his height.

1346
01:47:27,938 --> 01:47:29,146
It's irrelevant now.

1347
01:47:29,396 --> 01:47:31,146
The second is the way he sees.

1348
01:47:32,771 --> 01:47:36,188
Like a hungry tiger looks at a deer.

1349
01:47:37,271 --> 01:47:39,313
Not the way you are looking at me.

1350
01:47:42,563 --> 01:47:43,438
Look at me!

1351
01:47:44,396 --> 01:47:45,396
Look at my eyes.

1352
01:47:46,480 --> 01:47:48,021
The way I'm looking at you.

1353
01:47:51,896 --> 01:47:53,480
Third is his mannerisms…

1354
01:47:53,730 --> 01:47:54,813
His habits.

1355
01:47:58,230 --> 01:48:01,980
I very well know I can't beat
you at your own game, Sadhu.

1356
01:48:02,063 --> 01:48:03,896
That's why I used your game against you…

1357
01:48:05,605 --> 01:48:06,730
and played my game.

1358
01:48:08,063 --> 01:48:09,396
There's no electricity in that water.

1359
01:48:10,271 --> 01:48:12,563
You won't die even if you step in it.

1360
01:48:16,855 --> 01:48:17,771
I told you, right?

1361
01:48:18,230 --> 01:48:19,188
Mannerisms.

1362
01:48:20,355 --> 01:48:22,188
I was certain you'd
drink that water, Sadhu.

1363
01:48:23,355 --> 01:48:24,813
But the gamble is…

1364
01:48:26,271 --> 01:48:29,938
Will you drink the water
after or before killing me?

1365
01:48:39,230 --> 01:48:41,438
My game was never about
getting you into the water.

1366
01:48:42,980 --> 01:48:44,480
It was about making you
drink from that bottle.

1367
01:49:01,105 --> 01:49:02,146
It's too late, Sadhu.

1368
01:49:02,855 --> 01:49:07,271
You'll lose control of your body exactly
fifteen seconds after drinking it.

1369
01:49:09,146 --> 01:49:10,605
In the next 15 seconds,

1370
01:49:11,063 --> 01:49:12,855
your brain will stop working.

1371
01:49:14,063 --> 01:49:16,438
Only your dead body will remain later.

1372
01:49:21,730 --> 01:49:24,313
Well… played… Jay…

1373
01:50:15,438 --> 01:50:16,563
It's over now, Uncle.

1374
01:50:35,396 --> 01:50:39,271
When I was your age,
I had already lost my parents.

1375
01:50:41,438 --> 01:50:44,938
Just like you, I asked everyone
why it happened to them.

1376
01:50:47,730 --> 01:50:50,230
No one has answered me till today.

1377
01:50:52,021 --> 01:50:56,188
Maybe that's why, when you asked me,
I felt like answering.

1378
01:51:00,313 --> 01:51:01,896
Your father was killed, dear.

1379
01:51:05,855 --> 01:51:07,021
Who did it, Uncle?

1380
01:51:07,480 --> 01:51:09,771
I sent him to your father to apologize.

1381
01:51:11,896 --> 01:51:13,355
He must have apologized by now.

1382
01:51:16,605 --> 01:51:18,146
You know your father is no more.

1383
01:51:19,730 --> 01:51:21,230
You also know he won't come back.

1384
01:51:24,813 --> 01:51:26,271
Then why are you still waiting?

1385
01:51:37,063 --> 01:51:41,188
You promised to give me what I ask for
if I give you the answer.

1386
01:51:42,230 --> 01:51:43,896
- So, will you?
- Yes.

1387
01:51:45,105 --> 01:51:47,480
Please give me a smile.

